#
"AIR MAGUS" (Specialization)
===========================================================================
The Air Magus has mastered the elements of the air itself. They can
transform their very bodies into particles of air, making them difficult to
knock down. They may also transform an entire room into that similar to the
Air Plane, causing all in the room both the benefits and drawbacks of
battling on that terrain.

Innate Abilities
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
30th level:     Fly

Spells
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
10th circle:    Air Form
11th circle:    Ethereal Grounds

===========================================================================
See also: CONJURER, FLY, "AIR FORM", "ETHEREAL GROUNDS"

#
"AIRY WATER" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <room>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

"Airy Water" causes a bubble of breathable air to expand forth from the 
caster when he is submerged in a large body of water, making verbal 
communication and regular breathing possible.
===========================================================================
See also: "WATER BREATHING", WATERBREATH

#
ALCHEMIST (Sub-Class of: Magic-User)
===========================================================================
Alchemists are a class that can make things out of seemingly mundane
materials. They have the ability to craft items of all types including body
armor, rings, bracelets, etc. They also have the ability to forge weapons.
In addition to crafting and forging they can mix potions and throw them at
their enemies and at higher levels they are said to be capable of creating
scrolls and the ability to magically enhance items.   

Allowable races: 	Human, Gnome, Goblin, Orc.  		
Equipment usage:        Like all classes on Duris, alchemists have their
                        own specific item restrictions. They are restricted
                        in their use of weapons, mainly using maces, clubs
                        and staves. Some exceptions are allowed, however.
                        They can wear almost any type of armor, but are
                        mildly restricted in the use of miscellaneous
                        magical items.	
===========================================================================
See also: CRAFT, FORGE, MIX, SKILL_ALCHEMIST

#
ALIGNMENT (General Information)
===========================================================================
Your character's alignment (GOOD, NEUTRAL or EVIL) will govern how he or
she reacts to other players and/or monsters. The following is an outline of 
the alignment system:

&+WGOOD (350 to 1000)&n is the most prone to change (i.e., the hardest to
maintain). Killing other good-aligned players and monsters will harm it the
most, but killing neutrals can shift it towards evil as well.

&+GNEUTRAL (-349 to 349)&n is affected most by killing non-extreme
alignments (i.e., other neutrals). Killing extremes such as 1000 and -1000
is just maintaining the balance, and will have no effect on your alignment.

&+REVIL (-350 to -1000)&n is the most difficult to change. Almost anything
an evil person kills can be considered (at best) a neutral act, but it is
most likely the kill will just serve to make the person more evil. Only by
killing things more evil than oneself can one creep up out of the pit.

Alignment ranges from -1000 to 1000. Due to the way alignment works, before 
long your alignment will actually reflect your playing style, and will not 
fluctuate much unless you change your playing style drastically.
===========================================================================

