#
"ANIMATE DEAD" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <corpse>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Animation lasts until the undead follower dies (again)
Type of spell:  Summoning

"Animate Dead" allows the Necromancer to animate up to 12 corpses (the
precise number is dependent on the proficiency of the caster). The corpses
will follow the Necromancer for a limited time or until their destruction. 
A corpse can only be animated once.

There are whispered hints of further mysteries within this spell.
===========================================================================
See also: ORDER, PRESERVE, "MASS PRESERVE", PETS, EMBALM

#
ANSI COLORS (General Information)
===========================================================================
Duris is a world of color and in order to better understand how to add
color to certain things (such as guild titles) you need to know the ANSI
codes for it.

There are 3 basic types of ANSI color control sequences:

	&+<color>  -Sets the foreground color. If the letter is
                      uppercase, the color is bold.
	&-<color>  -Sets the background color. If the letter is
		      uppercase, the text will blink. 
	&=<bg><fg> -Sets both background <bg> and foreground <fg> color,
                      exactly as setting the background and foreground
                      separately.

Each color is specified using a letter. Black is L, red is R, cyan is C,
blue is B, white is W, green is G, yellow is Y, and magenta is M. To
specify the bright version of the color use the uppercase letter; for the
dark color, use the lowercase letter.

The actual colors themselves are as follows:

	&+WBright    &+LDark          &+WBright    &+LDark&n
	&+w--------------------------------------&n
	&+LBlack     &+lBlack         &+WWhite     &+wWhite&n
	&+RRed       &+rRed           &+GGreen     &+gGreen&n
	&+CCyan      &+cCyan          &+YYellow    &+yYellow&n
	&+BBlue      &+bBlue          &+MMagenta   &+mMagenta&n	
===========================================================================
See also: TESTCOLOR

#
"ANTI-PALADIN" "ANTI PALADIN" "ANTIPALADIN" (Sub-Class of: Fighter)
===========================================================================
Anti-Paladins are evil knights that have fallen from grace and now serve 
the darker powers of the world as a result. They, like their good-aligned
analogs the Paladins, are hearty Fighters that possess limited spell-like
powers. These powers are granted to them by their evil deities and are used
to further advance their vile causes.

Anti-Paladins are the best horsemen in the world. At higher levels, Anti-
Paladins receive many powers, primarily offensive in nature, and can
harm opponents with a touch.  

Allowable races:        Orc, Githyanki, Death Knight, Vampire.
Innate Abilities:       Summon Mount, Detect Evil, Detect Good, Vampiric
                        Touch  
Equipment Usage:	Like all classes on Duris, Anti-Paladins have their
                        own set of equipment they can use. Anti-Paladins
                        can use most weapons and armor,	but are rather
                        limited in their use of magic items.   
                             
===========================================================================
See also: FIGHTER, SKILL_ANTI-PALADIN, SKILLS, WEAPONS

#
APOCALYPSE (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <room>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

"Apocalypse" calls down the power of the four horsemen of death down upon
all not grouped with the caster. Victims of this spell can suffer from a
variety of nasty and unpredictable consequences should they fail to resist
it.
===========================================================================
See also: JUDGEMENT

#
"APPLY POISON" (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         apply poison <weapon_name>
Aggressive:     No

This skill allows the assassin to apply poison to a special weapon. If the
poison application is successful, there will be a chance of poisoning the
next creature attacked. This weapon must be re-poisoned after each battle.
===========================================================================
See also: POISON

#
APPRAISE (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         appraise <item>

This skill allows you to estimate the value of an item just by eyeballing
it.
===========================================================================

#
"ARCANE BLOCK" (Skill)
===========================================================================
With this skill, the Wizard has the potential to block some or possibly all 
of the effect of a magical attack. As the Wizard becomes more proficient in
this skill, he/she may block a greater deal of magical attacks to a larger
extent.
===========================================================================

#
"ARCANE RIPOSTE" (Skill)
===========================================================================
"Arcane Riposte" is similar to "Arcane Block", but, the Wizard has the 
chance to deflect aggressive spells being cast at him back to the caster.
As with "Arcane Block", this skill's success rate is dependent on the 
Wizard's proficiency.
===========================================================================

#
"ARCANE WHIRLWIND" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

"Arcane Whirlwind", when successful, transfers magic from the victim to 
the caster. Any and/or all magic the victim has, positive or negative,
may be potentially be stripped from the victim and granted to the caster.
===========================================================================

#
ARCHERY (Skill)
===========================================================================
This affects your ability to shoot arrows and bolts from any normal bow or
crossbow. You cannot shoot bows or crossbows without rudimentary knowledge
in this category.

NOTE: You must have arrows or bolts in a quiver, be wielding a bow and not 
be engaged in battle to use this skill.
===========================================================================
See also: "RANGE WEAPONS", FIRE, THROW

#
ARCHMAGE (MultiClass)
===========================================================================
An Archmage is a multi-class Conjurer/Sorcerer.

Both classes use memorize/spellbooks, so there is no change to how you
acquire/memorize/cast your spells when you multiclass.
===========================================================================
See Also: CONJURER, SORCERER, MULTI-CLASS, MEMORIZE

#
"AREA MAKING" AREAS BUILDING (General Information)
===========================================================================
The world of Duris is made up of various "zones" or areas, created by a
number of different people. Each zone is normally set around a theme, and
the levels intended for zones can vary greatly. Any player on Duris can
create a zone and submit it for approval. DikuEdit makes this much more
simple for the average player. To see a current list of zones, their
levels, and builders, type "credit".

Please email all zone submissions to: astansus@durismud.net
===========================================================================
See also: ZONES, WIZLIST, DIKUEDIT

#
"ARIEKS SHATTERING ICEBALL" ICEBALL (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Elemental

The legendary shaman Ariek discovered eons ago how to rapidly cool the air
before him and extract the moisture from it, almost instantly condensing 
it into a large, jagged and sharp ball of ice. The ball of ice then propels
itself blindingly fast towards its victim causing bloody wounds after
shattering.
===========================================================================

