Increases the attack speed of the wielder.
Wraps the wielder in a shell of stone.
Calls upon the chaotic power of darkness upon its wielder's foes, and protects
its wielder in various ways.

To see a list of artifacts and their owners, type "artifact".
===========================================================================
See also: UNIQUE, IOUN, FEEDING

#
ASSASSIN (Specialization)
===========================================================================
Assassins are practitioners of death and stealth, always lurking down dark
alleys and just around the corner, ready to commit a convenient act of
murder if it suits them. Assassins are adept at the art of concealment and
deception, but they are not as skilled at the art of stealth as other
related classes might be. Assassins are by far the most deadly creatures
around if they catch you by surprise and happen to be carrying their
favorite daggers with them.  

Skills
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
30th: Spinal Tap
40th: Apply Poison
45th: Control Flee
51st: Critical Stab

===========================================================================
See also: ROGUE, SKILL_ROGUE, CLASSES, SKILLS, THIEF, BRAVO

#
ASSIMILATE (Innate)
===========================================================================
Syntax: assimilate (while resting)

All Undeads, except for Gargoyles (Undead Harpies), must absorb their 
spells back into their minds via assimilate in order to cast them again.
===========================================================================
See also: "SPELL SLOTS", "SPELL SYSTEM", "SPELL CIRCLE", CASTER, CAST

#
ASSIST (General Information)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         assist <target>
Aggressive:     Yes

This command is used to come to the aid of a particular person, and you
begin fighting whomever (or whatever) they are fighting. It is useful to
prevent possibly deadly mistakes if there is more than one of a particular
monster in a room.
===========================================================================

#
"ASTRAL AFFINITY" (Innate)
===========================================================================
As the Psycheporter progresses in power, the inhabitants of his native 
plane become enamoured with him, and therefore resist the urge to attack.
===========================================================================
See also: PSYCHEPORTER, PLANE SHIFT

#
"AURA SIGHT" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <self>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster 
Type of spell:  Generic

Allows the caster to see auras surrounding living things not visible to the 
naked eye, as well as invisibility, the presence of life and farsight. The
effects bestowed by "Aura Sight" are dependent on the caster's level. All
possible effects are bestowed upon reaching 10th circle.
===========================================================================

#
AVATAR (General Information)
===========================================================================
An Avatar is created by the spell "channel", which requires four clerics
over level 50 to create. All four clerics begin casting the spell until the
avatar appears. It is then led by the lead cleric while the other three
clerics can only watch. The avatar itself is a level 56 cleric/warrior mob,
capable of all the spells and skills of those classes. The four clerics
themselves are left in a state of sleep until the avatar is lost or dies,
and their actual bodies are in no danger if the avatar is attacked.

Warning: If ANY one of the clerics that created the avatar loses link, the
avatar will be lost. 
===========================================================================
See also: CHANNEL

#
AVENGER (General Information)
===========================================================================
Avengers are the faithful servants of Gods, bringing justice to their evil
enemies. They are recruited from the most dedicated paladins willing to
sacrifice their lives entirely to the God's service. A Paladin becomes an
Avenger through Ascension, when he sacrifices the ability to enjoy mortal
pleasures and is imbued with God's might. Avengers no longer see like
other mortals, thus they cannot be blinded. They are surrounded by holy
light and their eyes emanate with internal glow. Rumors say they are able
to paralyze their foes solely through staring at them.
The Avengers can use all kinds of heavy armors but limit themselves to
powerful, 2-handed swords only. 

Allowable races:        Human, Half-Elf.
Equipment usage:        Like all classes on Duris, Avengers have their
                        own item restrictions. They can use most heavy
                        armor and weapons but are more limited in using
                        magical items.
Innate Abilities:	Inability to Blind, God Call, Magic Resistance.

===========================================================================
See also: SKILL_AVENGER

#
"AWAKEN FOREST" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <room>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Summoning

This spell causes the forest to waken and attack the enemies of the Druid.
Once roused, the forest will attack ungrouped players in the room, by 
hitting, bashing and potentially entangling them.

NOTE: "Awaken Forest" can only be cast in areas other than forest if the
"Grow" spell has already been cast.
===========================================================================
See also: BASH, ENTANGLE
 
#
AWARENESS (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         awareness

A person with awareness is protected somewhat from backstabs, bodyslams and
being stolen from, as well as heightening the senses somewhat. 
===========================================================================
See also: SNEAK, BACKSTAB, BODYSLAM, STEAL

#
"AWE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: Room 
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

This spell allows the caster to attempt to charm all living beings in the
same room. The amount of levels that can be charmed is based on the level
of the character and creatures above a certain level are not possible to 
control. 
===========================================================================

#
BACKSTAB (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         backstab <victim>

A backstab is an attempt to sneak up on the victim and place a weapon in
the victim's back at exactly the point where it will do the most damage. 
The amount of damage incurred is dependent on the proficiency of the
backstabber and the dice on the weapon used.

You may only backstab with piercing weapons. Assassins with good enough
proficiency at dual wielding weapons may double-backstab if they wield two
piercing weapons.
===========================================================================
See also: CIRCLE, "DUAL WIELD"

#
"BALLISTIC ATTACK" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim> | <victim><direction>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Psionic

This spell causes the caster to use his/her mind to create a boulder out of
thin air and hurl it at his/her victim with force.
===========================================================================

#
BANDAGE (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         bandage <victim>

The bandage skill can be used to save a player who is mortally wounded.
By bandaging, the player will begin to regenerate hitpoints once again, 
thereby saving their life. Players cannot bandage players while either
the bandager or the recipient is in combat.
===========================================================================

#
BANISH (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: Room
Aggressive: 	Yes
Cumulative: 	No
Duration: 	Instantaneous
Type of spell: 	Generic

The zealot will attempt to banish any charmed pets present by dissolving the 
energies that bind the summoned slave to this plane of existence. If the 
creature fails its saving throw and is of  elemental origin it will be sent 
back to its plane of existence, while undead slaves are destroyed. Purely
magical creations will simply cease to be.
===========================================================================

# 
BARBARIAN (General Information)
===========================================================================
Barbarians are ill-tempered beings that co-exist within clans of the
northern plains. They are sturdier and possess more stamina than their
smaller human counterparts, but have considerably less wit.
 
Class list:             Warrior, Shaman, Mercenary.
Statistics:             Barbarains are generally stronger and hardier than
                        Humans, but tend to trail them in all other areas.
Innate abilities:       bodyslam (warrior only), doorbash, breathe
Equipment Usage:	Barbarians have their own classification of item
                        restriction. They can use almost all weapons and 
                        most types of armor. But, they are limited in their 
                        use of magical items. 
                        
===========================================================================
See also: RACES, BODYSLAM, DOORBASH, INNATE, BREATHE

#
BARD (Sub-Class of: Rogue)
===========================================================================
Blessed with the talent of music, Bards can, with practice, play any
instrument. These instruments can invoke magical tunes and songs that act
as spells, aiding a party during their adventures. Bards are a thief/mage/
warrior hybrid by nature, and possess some of the advantages of all of
those classes. They are true "Jacks of all Trade" which means they have
many skills and spells, but are master of none.  

Allowable races:        Grey Elf, Drow Elf, Half-Elf, Human, Halfling,
			Goblin, Githyanki, Orc, Harpy
Innate abilities:       None
Equipment usage:        Like all classes on Duris, bards have their own set
                        of equipment they can use. Bards can use most
                        weapons, and armor, also many magic items.
===========================================================================
See also: PRACTICE, ROGUE, SKILL_BARD

#
BARKSKIN (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Protection

This spell causes the victim's skin to toughen and harden to the consistency 
of bark, granting a significant armor class improvement and slight 
protection from melee damage. This also means there is a somewhat higher 
increase in damage from fire.
===========================================================================

#
BASH (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         bash <victim>

To bash someone is to attempt to knock that person over. If you succeed,
you will inflict minor damage and cause the victim to fall down. Both you
and the victim will then be unable to respond to any commands for a short
duration. If you fail to bash successfully, you will lose your balance and
fall. It is more difficult to bash someone who is sitting/resting already,
although you can inflict greater damage. It is much easier to bash someone
if you are using a shield. Some creatures may be unbashable due to size or
other considerations.

NOTE: Bash will not work in places where there is no footing.
===========================================================================

#
BATTLEAID (Innate)
===========================================================================
Battleaid improves the potency of the Mercenary's "First Aid" and
"Bandage" skills, 
===========================================================================
See also: BANDAGE, "FIRST AID"

