#
BEASTMASTER (MultiClass)
===========================================================================
A Beastmaster is a multi-class Shaman/Druid.

Notes on Beastmaster:
Shamans use totems, and memorize spells without spellbooks.
Druids commune, which is heavilly based on terrain, for both spells
and commune times.
If you start as a Druid, you will commune all of your spells.
If you start as a Shaman, you will memorize spells, but you will no longer
need totems, for ANY of your spells.
===========================================================================
See Also: SHAMAN, DRUID, MULTI-CLASS, TOTEM, COMMUNE, MEMORIZE

#
BERSERK (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         berserk

Berserk represents a massive adrenaline rush and more or less mindless
rage, that has the following affects:

	Strength and Constitution increase.
	Dexterity and Agility decrease.
	Intelligence and Wisdom decrease.

As a result, you will most likely gain hits and do more damage. These 
changes to stats are based on your natural abilities and bonuses from
magic items or spells apply normally. This is one of the ways a stat can
exceed the 1-100 limit.

If you wish, you can start or stop a berserker rage by typing 'berserk',
level and skill heavily affect the results  f doing this. If a mob or
player walks into a room while you are berserked and not engaged in battle
at the time, you will automatically attack them. When berserk wears off,
you will lose the bonus hitpoints from Constitution and if this drops you 
below -10 hitpoints, you will die.
===========================================================================

#
BERSERKER (Sub-Class of: Fighter)
===========================================================================
Howling Screams, whirling whips, snacking on danger and dining on death. 
Berserkers attack in a focused battle rage that can grant them many
advantages on the battlefield. While at the same time their style tends to
be sloppier than that of warriors. Hence they tend to take more damage and
lack some skills with the shield. Many have been known to wield 2 handed
weapons with a fury almost unmatched. Their rage tends to focus themselves
totally on a single target at a time. So while in their younger years they
tend to attack more than warriors. As they age, they finally learn that
sometimes you must switch whom you fight. Bards sing of rumors that some
Berserkers have found a way to increase their size. If these stories are
true or not, it is not truly known. They are said to pray to the ancient
gods of the Nordic Lands. Such names as Odin, Loki, Thor, Beretorn, and
Kvasir. What powers are granted by these beings is a closely guarded
secret. Only the ancient dervish knows the true power that can be
unleashed. He dominates the Raven Realms dealing out death to those that
dare travel where they were never meant to be.

Allowable races:    Orc, Human
Equipment usage:    Like all classes on Duris, Berserkers have their own
                    item restrictions. They can use most heavy armor and
                    Non-slashing weapons but are more limited in using
                    magical items.

===========================================================================
See also: SKILL_BERSERKER

#
"BIGBY'S CLENCHED FIST" "BIGBYS CLENCHED FIST" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

This powerful spell causes a huge magical fist, five feet high, three feet
wide, to form before the caster. The fist strikes out at the victim with a
mighty blow, smashing into its target with dreadful force. The damage
sustained by the victim is not just from the crushing blow, but also from a
vicious shock wave that follows.
===========================================================================
See also: "BIGBYS CRUSHING HAND"

#
"BIGBYS CRUSHING HAND" "BIGBY'S CRUSHING HAND" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

This powerful spell causes an enormous, muscular-looking hand to appear 
before the caster. The hand grabs its victim and squeezes with a mighty 
force, causing the victim to suffer extensive bodily damage from broken 
bones and internal injuries.
===========================================================================
See also: "BIGBYS CLENCHED FIST"

#
BIND (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax: bind <name>

You can bind a player who is incapacitated or mortally wounded as long as
you are not wielding weapons and are holding a rope. When a player is bound,
he/she cannot move and may be drug about. If the bound player receives 
damage, he/she may become free of the binding. 
===========================================================================
See also: UNBIND, CAPTURE, DRAG

#
BIOFEEDBACK (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <caster>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Psionic

This impressive mental discipline causes the atmosphere surrounding the
caster to coalesce into a nearly solid vapor, making it extremely difficult
to cause physical harm to the protected person. Like all forms of
protection, the barrier can be worn down if repeatedly attacked enough.
===========================================================================
See also: "STONE SKIN"

