#
BRIGAND 
===========================================================================
The Brigand takes advantage of holes in the defense of the enemy, which 
can occur casting or clambering to their feet. He use these moments to deal 
crippling attacks to different parts of the body. And, with some luck, he 
may hit the victim's larynx, causing spell casters to abort. Or, stomp  the
victim's knees so that they have trouble running away.

Skills
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
36th level:     Ambush
46th level:     Crippling Strike
51st level:     Disruptive Blow

===========================================================================
See also: AMBUSH, "CRIPPLING STRIKE", "DISRUPTIVE BLOW", MERCENARY

#
BUG IDEA TYPO (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         bug <text>       (to report a bug)
                idea <text>      (to send an idea to the Gods of Duris)
                typo <text>      (to report a typo)

These commands are for making useful suggestions to the maintainers of the
game. 

Examples:

       bug The entire game crashes when I type "put 2.bag 2.bag".
       idea Put an inn in Verspin.
       typo In the room beside the oiled dragon: "sence" should be "sense".
===========================================================================
See also: PETITION

#
"BURNING HANDS" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Fire

"Burning Hands" causes a wide arc of flame to shoot forth from the
spell caster's fingertips, burning the victim.
===========================================================================

#
BURY (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax: drop <item>
        bury <item>

If you've used a shovel to dig a hole in the ground, you can drop the item
and use the 'bury' command to cover it up. You can then dig the item back
up later.

NOTE: Buried items will not survive crashes or reboots
===========================================================================
See also: DIG

#
BUY SELL (Command)
===========================================================================
These commands are used for making purchases or selling items in the
various shops found around Faerun. The prices in these shops will be
affected slightly by how personable you are and how charismatic you are.
===========================================================================
See also: SHOPS, VALUE, LIST, CHARISMA

#
CALENDAR MONTHS
===========================================================================
         (1) Month of Hammer (the Deepwinter)
         (2) Month of Alturiak (the Claws of the Cold)
         (3) Month of Ches (of the Sunsets)
         (4) Month of Tarsakh (of the Storms)
         (5) Month of Mirtul (the Melting)
         (6) Month of Bestanth (the Renewal)
         (7) Month of Kythorn (the Time of Flowers)
         (8) Month of Flamerule (Summertide)
         (9) Month of Eleasias (Highsun)
        (10) Month of Vinthar (of the Harvest)
        (11) Month of Eleint (the Fading)
        (12) Month of Marpenoth (Leafall)
        (13) Month of Uktar (the Rotting)
        (14) Month of Nightal (the Drawing Down)
        (15) Month of Mithrian (the Wanting)
        (16) Month of Horthos (of the Abandoned)
        (17) Month of Annaxes (the Breath of Frost)
===========================================================================
See also: DAY, TIME

#
"CALL LIGHTNING" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Electric

This spell causes a massive bolt of lightning to hurl itself from the rain 
clouds overhead, striking the intended victim and causing considerable 
damage. Storm Giants innately possess a stronger version of the Druid spell.
NOTE: Both the innate and the spell must be cast outdoors in order to work.
===========================================================================

#
"CALL OF THE GRAVE" (Skill)
===========================================================================
Drawing upon the power of the damned the Dreadlord shrieks out an ominous
chant, leaving the air thick and deathly still. Skeletons rise from their
cold graves within the earth beneath, tearing and clawing at the foe of 
their new Deathlord master, wreaking physical damage as they attempt to
bring them down.
===========================================================================
See also: DEATHLORD

#
CAMP (General Information)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         camp

When you are adventuring by road, it is often not advantageous to continue
your journey through the night, so Duris has a "Camp" option. Locate a safe 
place to camp for the night and then type "camp". You must then wait a
period of time before you can exit the game. If you leave the room in which 
you are trying to set up camp or if you fight, camping will automatically
cancel. Once you fully camp, you will be sent to the main menu, just as 
when you rent.

&+RWarning:&nIf you go link-dead, camping will stop (linkdead rent does 
        *not* reset your homeroom).
===========================================================================
See also: QUIT, RENT, LINK

#
"CANNIBALIZE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <caster>
Aggressive:     N/A
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Enchantment

This spell allows the caster to mentally absorb another being's innate
magical nature. The more damage the caster inflicts, the stronger his
'will' becomes.
===========================================================================

#
CAPTURE (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         capture <victim>
Aggressive:     yes

"Capture" attempts to grab and bind another player to drag in for a bounty. 
It enables the Mercenary to bind without first having to paralyze or 
incapacitate the victim. You be wielding no weapons and be holding a rope
for this to work.
===========================================================================
See also: BIND, UNBIND, DRAG

#
CARVE (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         carve corpse <body part>

When proficient in carve and armed with a knife, you can carve certain body
components from corpses. If you aren't very good at carving then you will
butcher some or most of the body parts you are trying to retrieve,
rendering them unrecognizable.
===========================================================================
See also: CORPSE, DECAY

#
CAST (General Information)
===========================================================================
Syntax: cast '<spell>' [<object> | <victim> ]

"Cast" is a command used to indicate that a spell is being created. It is
the act of invoking the gods or calling upon magical powers inside the
individual. Some spells may only be cast on the caster, and therefore you
do not need to indicate a target for the spell. If you are casting a spell
upon yourself, you may substitute for your name "me" or "self." All spell
names must be enclosed by ' '. For Magic-User subclasses, you must have a
spellbook containing the spell you want to cast in order to memorize it.
For Priest sub-classes, you may simply pray for your spells. Undeads, 
except for Gargoyles, must assimilate spells. Finally, Druids regain their
spells by communing them.

Examples:       cast 'burning hands' <victim>
                cast 'teleport'
                cast 'strength' me

If you are casting an offensive spell while in combat, and the target is
the enemy you are fighting, the spell will automatically be directed at the
enemy without having to define a target.

There is help available for each individual spell (see examples below).

Examples:      	help "cure light"
                help "minor creation"
                help "energy drain"

NOTE:  You can abbreviate the spell name when casting it.  For example,

                > cast 'lightning bolt' <monster>

                could be abbreviated as:

                > cast 'ligh' <monster>

You must be careful however when abbreviating to insure that the correct
spell is cast because many spells have similar names and the abbreviations
may not be obvious at once. Experimentation in a safe forum is the best
idea to insure that no disasters occur.
===========================================================================
See also: MAGIC, MEMORIZE, PRAY, ASSIMILATE, TUPOR, COMMUNE, CASTER, "SPELL SYSTEM", "SPELL SLOT", "SPELL CIRCLE", "SPELL FAILURE"

#
CASTER (General Information)
===========================================================================
"Caster" is a term that is used to described "Magic-User" and "Priest"
classes. It is used in referring to classes that are highly adept in the 
magical arts and who focus their studies solely on these crafts. Casters 
include Clerics, Conjurers, Warlocks, Ethermancers, Druids, Necromancers, 
Shamans, Psionicists, Illusionists and Sorcerers. Casters receive no 
penalties to their casting abilities.

The term "Semi-Caster" denotes an entirely different set of classes who, 
while not being as proficient in the magical arts, do dabble in the mystic 
areas. Because they do not devote their lives to the practice of magic, 
they have special hindrances. While being able to use many of the same 
spells as casters, semi-casters can only hold half the number of spells in
their repertoire that a caster of same level can. In addition, because they 
are not as trained in magic, they find it a bit more difficult to memorize 
their incantations and to call on their deities for divine powers. Hence, 
semi-casters must take a little additional time in preparing their magic. 
Semi-casters include Anti-Paladins, Paladins, Rangers, Reaver, Bards and
Unholy-Pipers.
===========================================================================
See also: MEMORIZE, PRAY, TUPOR, ASSIMILATE, COMMUNE, CAST, MAGIC, MYSTICS

#
