#
CENOBITE (MultiClass)
===========================================================================
A Cenobite is a multi-class Druid/Cleric.

Notes on Cenobite:
Druids commune, which is heavilly based on terrain, for both spells
and commune times.
Clerics pray, and require no spellbooks or totems.
If you start as a Druid, you will commune all your spells.
If you start as a Cleric, you will pray spells.
===========================================================================
See Also: CLERIC, DRUID, MULTI-CLASS, COMMUNE, PRAY
#
CENTAUR (General Information)
===========================================================================
Centaurs are a half horse, half human race, with the upper half looking
like a human, and the lower half looking like a large draft horse. Centaurs
are quiet, forest dwelling creatures from a far off forest covered land.
Centaurs are a good race, and thus will be on the good side of the race
wars on Duris. Being a seclusive race, centaurs are shy and slow to trust.
Because of this, only their own race and those of the elven and half-elven
race may enter their hometown. All other races are considered invaders,
and will be attacked on sight!

Centaur class list: Warrior, Ranger, Druid, Shaman.

Stats: Centaur are a very powerful race and have both great strength and
       hearty constitution. Being 1/2 horse, they can out-distance any
       other race in the world, being able to travel miles a day without
       growing tired. They are not known for their wit or wisdom however
       and thus seldom dabble in the mystic arts. They do however make
       decent Druids and Shamans, due to their high constitution. Centaur
       are so good with the bow that they gain a +2 to hit and a +1 on
       damage, due to their great strength. Their flighty nature and
       attunement with their environment allows them to be always AWARE and
       thus it is difficult to backstab them.

Centaur innate abilities: infravision, doorkick, stampede

Weakness: Centaurs are a flighty race by nature, and thus ALWAYS flee when
          they hear the roar of a dragon, and in fact, flee quite a lot.
          Also, given their odd body shape, Centaur cannot bash nor can
          they BE based by any race, save the Ogre, due to his great size
          and strength. Centaur can't wear anything on their legs, and can
          only wear horseshoes on their feet. They can however wear a ring
          on their tail.

Centaur have been known to sometimes allow their close friends to ride on 
their backs, but they must be wearing a saddle, and give consent.
===========================================================================
See also: RACES, INFRAVISION, INNATE, REAR-KICK, STAMPEDE, ARCHERY

#
"CHAIN LIGHTNING" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <room>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Electric

This spell is similar to the "Lightning Bolt" spell, except that the bolt
cast strikes multiple victims and is much more powerful and damaging.
===========================================================================
See also: "LIGHTNING BOLT"

#
"CHANNEL" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Channel is one of the most powerful s ells of a cleric and should be used
with great caution. It requires four clerics over level 50 to work, and
creates an avatar bringing the power of all the clerics together. First,
all the clerics must be grouped and consenting to "lead" cleric. They begin
casting the spell together until the avatar appears. The lead cleric then
takes control of the avatar, while the other clerics can simply watch. The
actual body of the clerics are left laying asleep where they are, but the
"lead" cleric, in avatar form, can move around, cast, etc.  

Warning: If ANY one of the clerics loses link during the avatar process,
the avatar will vanish. There IS a time limit on how often clerics can
avatar.
===========================================================================
See also: AVATAR

#
"CHANNEL NEGATIVE ENERGY" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

"Channel Negative Energy" causes a huge blast of raw negative planar energy
to emanate from the caster, striking his victim. The target suffers
considerable damage, and his lost vitality is transferred to the caster.
===========================================================================

#
CHANNELER (MultiClass)
===========================================================================
A Channeler is a multi-class Shaman/Conjurer.

Notes on Channeler:
Shamans use totems, and memorize spells without spellbooks.
Conjurers memorize and require spellbooks.
If you start as a Shaman, you will memorize spells, but you will no longer
need totems or spellbooks, for ANY of your spells.
If you start as a Conjurer, you will need spellbooks for all of your
conjurer AND your shaman spells.
===========================================================================
See Also: SHAMAN, CONJURER, MULTI-CLASS, TOTEMS, MEMORIZE

