#
CIRCLE (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         circle <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes

Circling is an attempt to backstab the opponent while in combat. This is
only possible if you are not tanking, i.e., the target of the opponent who
is taking the damage.

"Circle" also refers to spheres of knowledge of spell casting classes, with
higher circles denoting more powerful groups of spells. Spell casters (all
Mage and Priest sub-classes) and "semi-casters" (Rangers, Paladins, and
Anti-Paladins) gain in circle at levels 6, 11, 16, 21, 26, 31, 36, 41, and
46.
===========================================================================
See also: BACKSTAB, TANK, "SPELL CIRCLE"

#
CLASSES (General Information)
===========================================================================
Once you have selected the race of being you wish to play, you must select
a class. A class is the trade or profession at which your character will
excel. Not all classes are available for each race, as it would be highly
unlikely that an unintelligent, clumsy troll would take up the demanding
profession of assassin. There are four main "types" of classes (Fighters,
Priests, Rogues and Magic-Users) available, and the available classes are
listed below the headings of each one.

Fighter         Priest          Rogue           Magic-User
=======        ======         =====          ==========
Warrior         Cleric          Thief           Sorcerer
Ranger          Druid           Assassin        Necromancer
Paladin         Shaman          Mercenary       Conjurer
Anti-Paladin    Warlock         Bard            Psionicist
Monk            Ethermancer     Unholy-Piper    Illusionist
Reaver                                          Alchemist
Berserker
Dreadlord

NOTE: For more information on each class, type:
      "help <classname>" or "help skill_<classname>"
===========================================================================

#
CLERIC (Sub-Class of: Priest)
===========================================================================
Clerics are holy and powerful spell casters who obtain their magical power
from the gods and goddesses they worship. Their primary goal is to spread
the word of their faith and to bring good to the world. Most of the
Cleric's spell arsenal is defensive and healing in nature, making them one
of the most integral parts of a group.

Allowable races:        Human, Drow Elf, Grey Elf, Mountain Dwarf, Halfling, 
                        Half-Elf, Gnome, Orc, Goblin, Duergar Dwarf
Innate abilities:       God Call
Equipment usage:  	Like all classes on Duris, Clerics have their own
                        specific item restrictions. They are restricted in
                        their use of weapons, mainly using maces, clubs and
                        staves. Some exceptions	are allowed, however. They
                        can wear almost any type of armor, but are mildly
                        restricted in the use of miscellaneous magical
                        items.
                        
===========================================================================
See also: SKILL_CLERIC, PRAY

#
"CLERICAL SPELL KNOWLEDGE" (Skill)
===========================================================================
This skill lets you recognize and identify clerical-type spells as they are 
being cast by others. As you become more proficient in the category, you
will recognize more spells.
===========================================================================
See also: "SORCEROUS SPELL KNOWLEDGE", "SHAMAN SPELL KNOWLEDGE"

#
CLIMB (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         climb

Climb is used when you need to trek through mountainous terrain without the
benefit of flight spells. Climbing through mountains expends high numbers
of movement points, so, you may have to stop and rest. 

NOTE: Some mountains cannot be climbed.
===========================================================================

#
"CLOAK OF FEAR" (Spell)
