"CLONE FORM" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: Self
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Illusion

This is a more powerful version of mask allowing the caster to take on the
appearance of ANY mob or player in the room. Anyone with detect illusion
has a chance to see that this is an illusion

syntax: cast 'clone' victim name in room -to change your appearance
        cast 'clone' self or me -to remove the illusion 
===========================================================================
See also: MASK, "DETECT ILLUSION", DISGUISE

#
CODER (General Information)
===========================================================================
Coders of the MUD are a series of self correcting algorithms, usually the
process is started by a smaller script such as the "Alver", "Dvorak" or 
"Nokz" scripts. These work fine for most features but occasionally enter 
higher level functions and cause additional "features" which then need to 
pass through the "Tharkun" or "Ilienze" functions which restore the 
functions to their original code then rewrite them from scratch. The fabled 
Foo is a mostly unknown to Duris, but oddly his name is scratched to the 
bottom of each boat. If a Foo appears, most coder scripts will accept his 
function calls, except the "Kvark".
===========================================================================
See also: IMMORTALS, "ZONE GOD", WIZLIST, KVARK

#
COINS CURRENCY (General Information)
===========================================================================
Currency on Duris takes the form of coinage, and there are four types to be
found: &+Wplatinum&+w, &+Ygold&+w, &+csilver&+w, and &+ycopper&+w.&n

Note: coins are not weightless, so be careful in choosing how much to carry
around with you.  For example, 750 plat weighs 10 lbs.
===========================================================================
See also: EXCHANGE, BANKS

#
