HELP WHO NEWS MOTD TIME WIZLIST     | GET TAKE DROP PUT WEAR GRAB HOLD
CREDITS ATTRIBUTES SCORE WORLD      | REMOVE GIVE LOCK UNLOCK OPEN CLOSE
COMMANDS SPELLS LOOK EXAMINE        | FILL POUR TASTE EAT SIP DRINK
SEARCH EXITS MAP WEBSITE            | INVENTORY EQUIPMENT
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
&+yCombat:&n                             | &+GUtility:&n
KILL WIELD GLANCE GROUP DISBAND     | BUG IDEA TYPO QUIT SAVE RENT
CONSIDER PRACTICE TROPHY AGGR FLEE  | OFFER CAMP TOGGLE DISPLAY WRITE
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
&+MMonetary: &n                          | &+BCommon help subjects:&n
BALANCE DEPOSIT WITHDRAW EXCHANGE   | RACES, INNATE, RULES, PRACTICE,
BUY SELL LIST VALUE CURRENCY        | SPELLCAST, INDEX,
                                    | POLICIES, COMMANDS
                                    | <class>, <race>, <spell>, <skill>
===========================================================================
Further information is available by HELP <keyword>, with keyword being
a particular command or subject or class of subjects. Also, typing
"commands" on its own will produce a mechanical listing of the known verbs
performable from your current position. "commands ?" will give a list of
options for the command.
===========================================================================
See also: INDEX

#
COMMUNE (Skill)
===========================================================================
Unlike most spellcasters, Druids do not need to memorize or pray. They have
allied themselves with the natural world so well that they commune with 
their surroundings to derive the natural essence that is necessary for
their spells. This essence is more abundant in untamed wilds. What this
means is, Druids will regenerate their spells, while standing, at a rate that 
varies dependent on what terrain they are in.

Type 'commune' for a list of spells that are being regenerated back.
===========================================================================
See also: DRUID, TERRAIN

#
COMMUNICATIONS UTILITIES (General Information)
===========================================================================
The following is a list of all help available dealing with DurisMud
communications and utilities. An asterisk beside an entry indicates that
there is more help available at that entry. Type "help <entry>" for more
information.

Example: "help toggle" will bring up an explanation of the "toggle"
command, a list of all toggling options, and how to obtain further help on
each one.

  BUG IDEA TYPO         CONSENT                DISPLAY
  EMOTE :               GSAY                   IGNORE
  LANGUAGES             PASSWORD               PETITION
  READ                  BOARD                  DELETE REPEAT
  SHOUT                 SCORE ATTRIBUTES       SAY TELL WHISPER ASK '
  TOGGLE                WRITE                  
===========================================================================

#
CONCEALMENT (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim> | <object>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Enchantment

Concealment grants the target a limited form of invisibility, but it can be
broken by almost any action on the recipient's part. Concealment can be
detected with "Detect Invisibility", and can be dispelled by "Reveal True
Form" and "Faerie Fog".
===========================================================================
See also: "IMPROVED INVISIBILITY", "DECTECT INVISIBLE", "FAERIE FOG",
          "REVEAL TRUE FORM"

#
"CONE OF COLD" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim> | <victim> <direction>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Cold

"Cone of Cold" causes a huge cone of icy cold air to issue forth, freezing
the intended victim.
===========================================================================

#
"CONFUSE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: Room 
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous

This potent spell bathes all living things within the vision of the caster 
in pure mental confusion. This assault causes all exposed to it to react in
various manners. There is no way to determine how any individual will react
when thoroughly disoriented.
===========================================================================

#
"CONJURE AIR" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: One elemental
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Summoning

"Conjure Air" summons an elemental from the air plane which will follow 
the player as though charmed for a limited period of time. If the elemental 
is aggressive when the charm wears off, it will attack you and others.
===========================================================================

#
"CONJURE ELEMENTAL" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: One elemental
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Summoning

When cast, "Conjure Elemental" summons an elemental from a random elemental
plane which will follow the player as though charmed for a limited period
of time. There is no way to control which type of elemental is summoned.

If the elemental is aggressive when the charm wears off, it will attack you
and others.
===========================================================================
See also: "CONJURE GREATER ELEMENTAL"

#
"CONJURE GREATER ELEMENTAL" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: One elemental
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Summoning

Much more powerful version of the "conjure elemental" spell. This spell
summons a much larger and much stronger elemental than its counterpart,
"conjure elemental".
===========================================================================
See also: "CONJURE ELEMENTAL"

