#
CONJURER (Sub-Class of: Magic-User)
===========================================================================
Conjurers are the creative branch of the magic-users. They specialize in
enchantments, conjuring creatures and objects. They  re the only ones able
to identify objects. Conjurers, like other magic-users, possess awesome
spell casting might and are able to throw some of the world's most potent
spells. The conjuring style of magic first developed among the mixed breed
races, which would account for their smaller spell list and greater overall
spell potency.

Allowable races:        Human, Gnome, Grey Elf, Drow Elf, Orc, Goblin,
			Githyanki, Lich, Half Elf, Phantom, Shade.
Equipment usage:  	As all classes on Duris, Conjurers have their own
                        classification of item restriction. They have a
                        very small range of weapons they can use and a
                        small range of armor to choose from. They have very
                        little restrictions on what miscellaneous magical
                        items they can use, though.      
===========================================================================
See also: MAGIC-USER, PRACTICE, SKILL_CONJURER

#
"CONSECRATE LAND" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <room>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Enchantment

"Consecrate Land", when cast outdoors, blesses the land on which it is
cast. This (temporarily) sacred land heals anyone upon it at an increased
rate. In addition, all damage dealt in this room is reduced.
===========================================================================

#
CONSENT (General Information)
===========================================================================
"Consent" is a check performed by the MUD code in order to confirm that a
player (victim) is agreeing to the action being performed upon him or her
by another player.

Usage:
consent <name> -you give your undying trust to <name>
consent        -you revoke consent
consent who    -lists all players that have given you consent

You may only consent to one person at a time, but you can change it as
often as you wish. The person you are consenting to need not be in the
room with you, but you must be able to see him/her. (If who <name> doesn't
work, neither will consent <name>).
===========================================================================
See also: GROUP

#
CONSIDER (General Information)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         consider <opponent>

This command will compare your character's level with that of the monster's
or player's and give you a rough estimate of your chances of defeating it. 
This estimate is by no means exact and does not take hit points, special 
attacks or damage into consideration.

Example:        consider dog
===========================================================================

#
CONSTITUTION (General Information)
===========================================================================
Constitution is a measure of your overall health and hardiness, how well
you resist adverse conditions and strains. To reflect this, a high
constitution can increase your number of hitpoints. All classes benefit 
from high constitution, but Warrior classes more so than others.
===========================================================================
See also: STATISTICS, "ENHANCE CONSTITUTION"

#
CONSTRUCT (Command)
===========================================================================
Construct is the basis for building both houses and guildhalls. Funds must
be kept on hand while using this command. It takes a varying amount of
money and time to construct something, dependent on where you would like to
build it. Everything is saved through a crash, though, so fear not.

&+Yconstruct guildhall&n
  Cost: varies on terrain
  This will construct your guildhall on the current worldmap location you
  are standing on.  Only Leaders have this ability.  The guildhall will
  be a down exit from your current location and will consist of two rooms.

&+Yconstruct room <exit dir> <door|nodoor> [door keyword]&n
  Cost: 1k
  This option will build a room with an exit from the room you are standing
  in into the new room. You must use a valid exit direction <n s e w> and
  tell it if you want a door or nodoor. If you want a door, you should
  specify the keyword. e.g.: construct n door curtain
  &+RNote: The doors are bugged, do not use them&n

Once you have the initial building in place, there are various addictions
available for you.

&+Yconstruct name <&+WA&+Bn&+Ms&+Gi&n room name>&n
  Cost: 50     
  Names the current room. You are able to use ANSI color in this.

&+Yconstruct describe&n
  Cost: 10
  This option will put you into the edit system similar to bulletin
  boards, and when you are done will set the description of the room
  appropriately.

&+Yconstruct inn &+RDISABLED&n
  Cost: 5k
  Builds an inn in the current room. Only one inn is allowed per guildhall.
  &+RNote: Inns are disabled we don't want want the hometowns ignored.&n

&+Yconstruct heal&n
  Cost: 3k
  Builds a accelerated healing room in the current room.

&+Yconstruct teleporter <target>&n
  Cost: 20k
  Builds a teleporter between two halls. You must have a target standing 
  in the room of the other hall, and this command will build the teleporter
  from your room to his room and back. A guild may have up to 2 teleporters
  per hall, but the guildhall must contain 10 rooms before a teleporter
  can be placed within it.

&+Yconstruct mouth &+RDISABLED&n
  Cost: 500
  Builds a magic mouth in current room. This acts as an alarm and will
  broadcast when someone not in your guild is in that room. Only one
  magic mouth can be built per guildhall.

&+Yconstruct fountain&n
  Cost: 500
  Builds a fountain in current room. Only one fountain of any type may be
  built per guildhall.

&+Yconstruct holy|unholy&n
  Cost: 3k
  Builds a holy/unholy fountain in the current room. Only one fountain of 
  any type may be built per guildhall.

&+Yconstruct cabinet &+RDISABLED&n
  Cost: 2,500  
  This option will create a cabinet in the house (not available for use in
  guildhalls, please use construct chest), allowing you to store things in
  it. Any number of cabinets can be built.

&+Yconstruct chest &+RDISABLED&n
  Cost: 5k
  Builds a chest in the current room. Any number of chests may be in each 
  room and guildhall.
  &+RNote: Chests have been replaced with guild lockers in hometowns.&n

&+Yconstruct shop &+RDISABLED&n
  Cost: 10k
  Builds a shop in the current room.
  &+RNote: Shops are disabled we don't want want the hometowns ignored.&n

&+Yconstruct secret entrance &+RDISABLED&n
  Cost: 10,000 
  This option will hide the entrance to your house (not available for
  guildhalls).

&+Yconstruct cleric | mage | warrior&n
  Cost: 10k
  Used to construct mage, cleric, or warrior golems. Golems will be placed
  in the entryway of your guild, no matter where you execute this command.
  Only 4 golems can be built per guildhall.

Note: Many commands may now be used to move options from one room to
another. Doing a new "construct fountain" for example will cost 0, and will
move the fountain spot to your current room. All moves of this sort will
take place the next time the game reboots.

===========================================================================
See also: GUILD, GUILDHALL, SOCIETY

