#
"DEATH KNIGHT" (General Information)
===========================================================================
The Death Knight is a twisted form of a Lich. A race of undead warriors
spawned by a demon prince (popular thought credits Demogorgon), from fallen
human paladins. No one knows exactly why this was done except for the
obvious explanation: The raising of an army that was never used. The
perverted soul of the former paladin lives through eternal torment in its
undead state, killing anything that will satisfy its rage at what has been
done to it.

Allowable races:       Anti-paladin, Warrior, Mercenary.

Death knight stats:    Unlike Liches, Death Knights wear heavy armor and 
                       the weapons of warriors. They will usually be riding
                       a nightmare which they often summon to do their
                       bidding.

Innate abilities: Ultravision, summon mount, anti-good, vampiric touch,
                  fireball, fireshield, firestorm, protection from fire
===========================================================================
See also: ANTI-PALADIN, SKILL_ANTI-PALADIN

#
DEATHLORD (Specialization)
===========================================================================
The Deathlord is a creature of destruction and doom, it thrives on the 
moments when 'life' hangs in the delicate balance of fate. Their very souls
feed from the powers of death and decay, bringing the chill of the undead
to the world around them.

Skills
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
21st level:    Call of the Grave
31st level:    Embrace Death
36th level:    Soul Trap

Please note, this is a new spec, some sections may still be under review
and development, and as such are liable to changes.

===========================================================================
See also: DREADLORD, SKILL_DREADLORD, SPEC_LIST, "CALL OF THE GRAVE",
          "EMBRACE DEATH", "SOUL TRAP"

#
DECAY (General Information)
===========================================================================
After a set amount of time all corpses will decay. Corpses of NPCs will
decay and leave the equipment scattered on the floor. After a crash or
reboot, these corpses are not loaded. Corpses of players will decay in time
following a death. The equipment will also be scattered on the ground. So,
following a death, it is important to retrieve your corpse in a timely
manner. Corpses of players will, however, load after a reboot or crash. 
Player corpses currently decay after approximately 2 hours. The decay time 
is reset if the game reboots or crashes before the corpse has decayed. The
spells preserve and embalm may prolong the time until a corpse decays.
===========================================================================
See also: REBOOT, CRASH, PRESERVE, EMBALM, RESURRECT, DEATH

#
DECREPIFY (Innate)
===========================================================================
By dark ritual the character is surrounded by a dark aura of power. When
a victim comes into contact with this aura it will weaken their defenses
versus all sorts of magic allowing their enemies a stronger chance of 
winning.
===========================================================================
See also: ANTI-PALADIN, INNATE

