#
EMOTE
===========================================================================
Syntax:  emote <message_text>
         : <message_text>

The "emote" command allows you to creatively pretend that your
character is doing something that the available socials do not
currently allow.  For example, if Fizzwig wished everyone to think he
is a really nice guy, he might type:

        emote hands you 10000 pcoins.
                -or-
        : hands you 10000 pcoins.

This would be viewed as everyone in the room as:

        Fizzwig hands you 10000 pcoins.

Of course, Fizzwig has not really given anyone the coins, he just
wants everyone to think he has.

A quicker, equivalent command is ":"

Note:  "emote" is a social action that is used for *fun*.  Please do not
take these actions seriously.
===========================================================================
See also: "SOCIAL ACTIONS"

#
ENCHANT (Skill)
===========================================================================
This skill will imbue a piece of equipment of your choosing with any spell
up to a certain power that is currently affecting the casting alchemist.
There are some restrictions in the type of spells that may be enchanted;
Offensive spells or any spells that are of the "self only" cast type cannot
be enchanted into the item. Only one enchant affect can be held on a piece
of equipment at any one time and the effect will wear off in the
appropriate time span. Enchanting an item can be an expensive exercise and
you will need to carry the necessary funds to use this skill. An enchanted
item will display a flag indicating that status if successful, however, 
beware that unsuccessful enchant attempts may actually damage the item in 
the process. Example Syntax: enchant cloak 'vitality'
===========================================================================
See also: ALCHEMIST, SKILL_ALCHEMIST

#
ENCHANTER (MultiClass)
===========================================================================
An Enchanter is a multi-class Bard/Sorcerer.

Both classes use memorize/spellbooks, so there is no change to how you
acquire/memorize/cast your spells when you multiclass.
===========================================================================
See Also: BARD, SORCERER, MULTI-CLASS, MEMORIZE

#
ENCRUST
===========================================================================
Encrusting is one of the highly sought after skills of the Alchemist Class.
By collecting various rare gems, the alchemist can bind into other
equipment items the power of these stones.

The stones themselves can sometimes be found in the corpses of the more
fearsome and hard to kill creatures of Duris.

You will need to make sure that the equipment item and the stone you wish
to use for the "encrust" are both in your inventory then type:

     encrust item stone

For example if you have "a strange Green stone", and "a steel dagger", just
make sure both are in your inventory then type: encrust dagger stone

Warning: Encrusting an item, overwrites all existing proc's for that item.
===========================================================================

#
