#
EQUIPMENT
===========================================================================
Typing "equipment" will allow you to view what items you are wearing and
where you are wearing them. For example:

> equipment

<worn around neck>      a shiny black cape
<worn on finger>        a red ring
<wielded>               a sword

This command can be shorted to simply "eq".
===========================================================================
See also: INVENTORY

#
EVASION (Innate)
===========================================================================
This extraordinary ability allows the target of an area spell attack to 
twist out of the way avoiding all damage. 
===========================================================================
See also: SPELL

#
EXAMINE (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         examine <victim> | <object>

"Examine" may give you some valuable information about an item or 
character. It will also tell you what is inside a container, if it is open.  
When there is more than one object or character of the same name in the 
room and you wish to examine each one, use the following example as a 
guideline:

You are in a room and you see:

        An ugly, drooling frog is standing here.
        An ugly, drooling frog is standing here.
        An ugly, drooling frog is standing here.

You wish to examine each one.  You would type:

        examine frog
        examine 2.frog
        examine 3.frog
===========================================================================
See also: LOOK

#
EXCHANGE BANKS BALANCE DEPOSIT WITHDRAW
===========================================================================
Banks can be found throughout the Realms, and it is the wise adventurer 
indeed that utilizes them often. Carrying large amounts of money around
with you can be hazardous: you could not only lose the cash you are
carrying if you die, but you would also be welcome prey to any thief.

You can also "exchange" the money that you are carrying for that of smaller
or higher denominations, usually for some surcharge. See below for correct
syntax.

The following commands can be used at any banks:

        BALANCE
        DEPOSIT <amount> <coin_type>
        WITHDRAW <amount> <coin_type>
        EXCHANGE <amount> <coin_type> <desired_coin_type>

Examples of monetary exchange:

        exchange 1000 gcoins pcoins
        exchange 1000 copper platinum
        exchange 5 platinum scoin
        
The standard Duris currency values equate as:

        10 copper =1 silver
        10 silver =1 gold
        10 gold =1 platinum
        
        Be aware that many banks will have a higher exchange rate as they
        like to charge an processing fee!
        
===========================================================================
See also: COINS, CURRENCY

#
EXITS
===========================================================================
Typing "exits" will give you a list of all the obvious exits from your
location.  The more obscure routes, if any, won't be as perceptible.
You will have to use a little ingenuity to locate those.
===========================================================================

#
EXPERIENCE XP EXP LEVELS (General Information)
===========================================================================
Syntax:   exp (to see how much experience you currently have)

Whenever you kill a monster or a player, you earn experience points. Once 
you have earned enough experience, you raise a level in your class. Duris 
has 56 mortal levels; you can check your progress by typing 'experience'.  
The levels after 50 are only received by quaffing a specific potion, found 
in zones.

Here are a few things you should know about experience points:

	-Each pulse you hit or miss a monster when you are engaged
	  you get experience points. 
	-Healing a person who is in combat and grouped with you will 
	  give you a lot of experience points.
   	-You get exp for each spell you cast upon a monster or a player
	  in your group if you are in combat. The amount of experience
 	  points received depends on which circle the spells is in. You
	  also receive experience points for using skills in combat, such
	  as bash, backstab, kick and so on.
	-If you kill a monster of a higher level than yourself, you get 
 	  bonus experience points.
	-If you kill a monster of a lower level, you will gain less 
          experience points.
	
===========================================================================
See also: GROUP, TROPHY, DEATH

#
