#
FEEDING (General Information)
===========================================================================
On Duris, artifacts, uniques, and iouns are in need of "feeding", which
means killing someone of the opposite racewar in order to gain a full frag.
You must reach one full frag to sate your artifact within a number of days
which varies between each item.  If you fail to feed, your artifact will
be removed and placed back into the game where it loads, if any.
===========================================================================
See also: ARTIFACT, UNIQUE, IOUN

#
"FEIGN DEATH" FEIGNDEATH (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         feign death

"Feign Death" is a rather clever way of fooling all those nearby into 
believing that you have died. In actuality, you are alive a d in hiding. 
You then have a good chance of escaping in one piece since only the most 
astute of enemies can determine that you are still alive.
===========================================================================

#
"FERRIX PRECISION" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: Self
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Protection

This will increase your precision, increasing your dexterity and ability
to hit more often and accurately.
===========================================================================

#
FIGHTER (General Information)
===========================================================================
The Fighter, as the name suggests, is a class that involves hand-to-hand 
combat most extensively. They are usually the first to charge into battle 
and are almost always the ones that stand at the head of a fighting group 
("acting as tank," it is commonly called). They sustain most of the battle 
damage.

Fighters represent a group of classes into which Berserkers, Warriors,
Rangers, Reavers, Paladins, Anti-Paladins, Monks and Dreadlords are grouped. 
Each sub-class has its own experience chart according to which they gain 
levels.

NOTE: Use "help <classname>" for information on each of the sub-classes.
===========================================================================
See also: WARRIOR, RANGER, PALADIN, ANTI-PALADIN, BERSERKER, REAVER, MONK,
          DREADLORD, TANK, CLASSES, SKILLS

#
FILL
===========================================================================
Syntax:  fill <to-drink_container> <from-drink_container>

         Examples:
         fill skin pool
         fill barrel fountain

This command lets you refill your drink container from another source.
Note that you cannot mix liquids.
===========================================================================
See also: EAT DRINK SIP TASTE, POUR

# 
FIRE (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:    fire <missile> <target> <direction>

To fire a weapon you must be wielding a firing weapon (bow, crossbow, etc) 
and have a quiver with ammunition. You must possess the correct type of 
missile for your particular weapon in order to be able to fire. The number 
of missiles fired depend on the weapon. Elves tend to be very good with 
range weapons.
===========================================================================
See also: "RANGE WEAPONS", THROW

