#
FOLLOW (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:  follow <character>
         toggle follow

If two or more players decide to travel in the same direction, why not
have one of them lead and the rest follow?

For example:

Fizzwig and Manwich decide to go to visit the Sorcerers Guild. Fizzwig 
follows Manwich by typing:

        'follow manwich'

Manwich then leads the way and Fizzwig just sits back and enjoys the 
scenery. Once Fizzwig gets tired of following Manwich around, she can just 
type:

        follow me
           -OR-
        follow self
           -OR-
        follow fizzwig
===========================================================================
See also: GROUP 

#
"FOLLOW-UP RIPOSTE" (Skill)
===========================================================================
Specialized Warriors have the additional reflexive ability for an extra
damage riposte. A riposte is a fencing move made when you successfully 
parry your opponent's attack and manage to score a minor hit of your own in 
reply. The success of your riposte depends heavily on the success of your 
parry.
===========================================================================
See also: RIPOSTE

#
FORAGE (General Information)
===========================================================================
Syntax: forage

"Ingredients" are located throughout the world of Duris, buried under the
ground. In order to retrieve these ingredients, you must "Forage" for them.
Some classes, such as Alchemists and Forest Druids (specialized Druids),
need specific ingredients in order to cast spells or mix potions.

&+RWarning:&n While foraging, you cannot enter new commands for a period of 
        time, making you prone to attack. So, be sure you are relatively 
        safe before foraging!
===========================================================================
See also: ALCHEMIST, INGREDIENTS, "FOREST DRUID"

