#
FRAGS (General Information)
===========================================================================
Syntax:     frag 
            frag <classname>
            frag <racename>
            frag <racewarsidename>

The term "frag", originally taken from the Vietnam War, is when you kill 
another player. Every time you kill someone who is an opposite racewar side,
(a Human killing a Drow, etc), you get a frag. Every time you are killed by 
someone who is an opposite racewar side, (a Phantom being killed by a 
Drow), you lose a frag. All frags are split between the group equally. So,
if you are with a group of five people and you kill one player, you will
each receive .20 frags. For each player killed, there is a total of 1.00
frags to be split among the grouped victors. Typing "fraglist"  will show
a list of the top ten and lowest ten fraggers in the mud. Or, you may type
"frag <racewarside>", "frag <classname>" or "<frag racename>".
===========================================================================
See also: TROPHY

#
