"GATE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: Room
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Dependant upon level of caster
Type of spell:  Teleportation

"Gate" is a rather powerful spell which creates a multidirectional 
portal to another plane of existence.  The destination of the gate
is totally random and cannot be directed.

The planes that may be directly gated are:

	-&+yThe Elemental Plane Of Earth&N
	-&+bThe Elemental Plane Of Water&N
	-&+CThe Elemental Plane Of Air&N
	-&+rThe Elemental Plane Of Fire&N
	-&+RThe Plane Of Avernus On The Nine Hells&N
	-&+LThe Negative Material Plane&N
	-&+LThe Ethereal Plane&N
	-The Astral Plane
===========================================================================

#
GAZE (Skill)
===========================================================================
The gaping empty sockets of the Dreadlord may be sightless, but its gaze
contains something much more searching, disturbing and terrifying than most
mortals may bear. To have the gaze of a Dreadlord upon you is to know true
fear. Too petrified to move, your world ceasing and stopping as you
struggle to free and turn away. The ability to gaze is dependant on the 
attribute power of the attacker. It is not crucial but will help subdue 
the victim.
===========================================================================
See also: DREADLORD, SKILL_DREADLORD

#
GET TAKE (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:        get <object> | take <object>

If you are in a hurry, or if you feel greedy, you can type get all. You can 
also use "get" and "take" to extract objects from containers.

Example:  "get dagger from bag" or more simply, "get dagger bag".

When there is more than one object of the same name in the container or room 
and you wish to get a particular one, use the following example as a 
guideline:

You are in a room and you see:

        A shiny box is lying in the dirt here.
        A shiny box is lying in the dirt here.

If you wished to get the second box, you would type:

        "get 2.box"
===========================================================================
See also: DROP, PUT

#
GITHYANKI
===========================================================================
Coming from the Astral plane, this race of evil humanoids were slaves of
the Illtihid race millennia ago. The Githyanki broke away from their former 
masters after learning many of their mental powers, and learning how to be 
pure evil.

Githyanki HATE their former masters more then anything and will instantly
attack them on site! Giths will go out of their way to hunt down and
kill any illithid they can find. Githyanki do not have a normal hometown
but must start on the astral plane, in a fortress of Githyanki there. As
newly adult Giths they must now venture to the prime plane and make a
name for themselves.

Githyanki look much like humans only slightly taller, much more thin, with
faces that resemble a decomposing corpse. They tend to be ruthless and
significantly smarter than humans.

Class list:       Warrior, Anti-Paladin, Sorcerer, Necromancer, Bard,
                  Psionicist, Conjurer.       
Innate abilities: levitate, ultravision, shift_prime, shift_astral

&+RWarning:&n  As one of the eight evil races on Duris, the Githyanki are
extremely difficult to play and face many hardships.  Their hometown
has been specifically designed to make life hell and death waits
around every corner.  Githyanki will most certainly encounter situations
that would be deemed "unfair" to any of the surface races.  We did
this to create a new challenge for those advanced players who have
"beaten" the challenge of life on the surface world and are looking
for something more difficult.  You should NOT play a Githyanki unless you
are a *very* advanced player and are used to the Duris style of
MUDding, or are willing to face the hardships without complaint, as it
will NOT be easy.
===========================================================================
See also: RACES, LEVITATE, NECROMANCER, SORCERER, ANTIPALADIN,
           WARRIOR, PSIONICIST

#
GIVE
===========================================================================
Syntax:  give <object> <target>

If you feel charitable, you may want to give items to someone in need.

Example:  "give bread beggar"

Money, in the form of various types of coinage, is a little more
difficult to give away.

Syntax:  give <amount> <coin_type> <target>

Giving very heavy objects, or 1000s of coins, or anything that will
overload the receiver, requires the receiver's consent.
===========================================================================
See also: COINS CURRENCY CONSENT

#
GLADIATOR (MultiClass)
===========================================================================
A Gladiator is a multi-class Mercenary/Warrior.
===========================================================================
See Also: MERCENARY, WARRIOR, MULTI-CLASS

#
GLANCE
===========================================================================
Syntax: glance [opponent]
        glance <target>

While in battle, it is often advantageous to check the health condition of
your comrades or the mob that you are fighting. Instead of using the "look"
command, which will list all the equipment the player or mob is wearing,
use the "glance" command. This command will provide you with a synopsis of
the current health of the mob or player that you are glancing at. Others
cannot see you glancing.
===========================================================================
See also: LOOK

#
"GLOBE OF DARKNESS" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: Room
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

"Globe of Darkness" creates a globe to appear over the casters' head which
emanates total darkness around the room.  The dark globe travels with the 
caster until its duration expires or it is cancelled by "mage flame".
===========================================================================
See also: "MAGE FLAME"

#
"GLOBE OF INVULNERABILITY" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Protection

"Globe of Invulnerability" encases the victim in a powerful energy barrier 
which is capable of blocking a great deal of spells. The number of blocked 
attacks upon the globe has no affect on its duration, and the globe 
provides no protection at all from physical assault.
===========================================================================
See also: "MINOR GLOBE OF INVULNERABILITY", "GROUP GLOBE OF INVULNERABILITY"

#
GMOTD
===========================================================================
This command gives you your Guild Message Of The Day, otherwise known as
the news flashes for your guild that you see when you log in.

Setting up your GMOTD: Only guild leaders are able to change and set your
guild's GMOTD. To do this the leader writes the motd onto a piece of paper
(which can be minor c'ed) and then type 'gmotd paper' to activate it. If
you just type 'gmotd' or you are not a leader, it will show your current
guild motd.
===========================================================================
See also: NEWS, GMOTD

#
GNOME
===========================================================================
Gnomes are small, sturdy humanoids who are well known for their quick hands
and good humor. Smaller and weaker than humans, gnomes have more wit to
compensate. Gnomes have colonies of their own, but are commonplace among
the major surface communities. Gnomes and dwarves are distantly related,
and gnomes often understand dwarves fairly well. Gnomes have permanent
infravision.

Classes:    Warrior, Cleric, Shaman, Sorcerer, Conjurer, Thief, Alchemist,
            Illusionist.
Statistics: Gnomes have very quick minds, but seem to lack the wisdom to
            use that intelligence well. Their bodies are also fairly quick,
            which is probably good, because they are also weak, and not
            very appealing.
Innates:    Infravision, Farsee.
===========================================================================
See also: RACES, INFRAVISION, INNATE

#
GOBLIN
===========================================================================
Goblins are an inhospitable, evil race that prefers to dwell deep within
the depths of the Underdark. They live in a largely tribal society where
the strongest rule over the rest, existing preferably in underground caves
and similar dismal surroundings. Despite their primitive habitat they are a
rather clever and devious people that have mastered many of the same skills
and magics of the sun-loving races. Goblins are avid slavers and routinely
capture others to serve at their bidding, especially gnomes and mountain
dwarves whom they hate more than anything else.

Goblins range in appearance from a dark, dull green to a dull orange or
brick red. It is rumored that Goblins are distantly related to the Kobolds,
but to this day that claim has yet to be proven.

Class list:       Warrior, Cleric, Shaman, Sorcerer, Necromancer, Reaver,
                  Conjurer, Thief, Assassin, Mercenary, Bard, Alchemist,
                  Illusionist.
Statistics:       Goblins are a very intelligent people, therefore they
                  have become a feared race of proficient casters. They are
                  also quite nimble, making them naturals at stealing and
                  stealth.
Innate abilities: ultravision, flurry, disappear.

Warning: As one of the evil races on Duris, Goblins are extremely difficult
to play and face many hardships. Their hometown has been specifically
designed to make life hell and death waits around every corner. Goblins
will most certainly encounter situations that would be deemed "unfair" to
any of the surface races. We did this to create a new challenge for those
advanced players who have "beaten" the challenge of life on the surface
world and are looking for something more difficult. You should NOT play a
Goblin unless you are a *very* advanced player and are used to the Duris
style of MUDding, or are willing to face the hardships without complaint,
as it will NOT be easy.
===========================================================================
See also: RACES, ULTRAVISION, INFRAVISION, INNATE

#
"GOD CALL" (Innate)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         innate god call

The Cleric has the ability to call upon their God to come to their aid.
Before specialization, this ability will have one of three effects. After
specialization, it will have only one effect.

Zealot:
The zealot will call upon the gods to strengthen him in the ways of combat.
For the duration the cleric will gain melee attacks and also receive a
boost to his hitroll and damroll. 

Holyman:
The blessing of the gods will blanket the room with peace causing all 
players and npc characters to disengage from combat. It will also clear all 
the mobs tracking the cleric.

Healer:
Using the god call as a healer will result in a powerful uninterruptible 
heal that can take form in two different ways. If the god call is used
without a target it will heal every person in the group by 200 hitpoints. 
If it is used with a target it will heal that person 600 hitpoints. 
===========================================================================
See also: SPEC_LIST, CLERIC, ZEALOT, HOLYMAN, HEALER

#
"GOD, COMMANDS"
===========================================================================
The format to access help for god commands is structured as follows:

     help god, <command>

Help on the following god commands and god information areas is available:

accept, decline, advance, advancement, at, cheating, clone, debug, demote,
echo, echoa, echoz, finger, force, freeze, goto, grant, revoke, gshout,
ingame, inroom, knowledge, levels, lightning, load, lookup, pardon,
participation, pflags, poofin, poofout, ptell, purge, reinitphys, release,
restore, secret, setattr, setbit, sethome, silence, snoop, snowball,
spells, stat, string, supervise, switch, return, teleport, title, trans,
users, vis, where, wizhelp, wizloc, wizmsg
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, ACCEPT" "GOD, DECLINE"
===========================================================================
Syntax:  accept <charname|on|off>
         decline <player> [<reason>]

These commands let you accept or decline potential character's names,
dependent on whether they meet up to the standards set forth in the
introduction at new character creation. "accept off" turns this acception/
decline mode off, and simply allows new characters to log on without a
god's permission.
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, ADVANCE"
===========================================================================
To promote a player to a level higher than they currently have. The default
is to advance one level. A level 0 player is always only advanced by one
level. *ONLY* Forgers are allowed to advance players on Duris. If you have
a question regarding this ruling, please contact one of the forgers.

For a current list of the Forgers, type "wizlist"
===========================================================================
See also: WIZLIST

#
"GOD, ADVANCEMENT"
===========================================================================
As it is with human nature, we all strive to obtain excellence in what
we do.  We have yet to meet a person who does not wish to be top dog,
and this is fine.

On Duris, we encourage you to participate and add to our MUD in some shape
or form. All those who add to it in a significant way will be moved up in
the chain of command. It will not be easy to move up the ladder, though.

Remember, having your god is a privilege, not a right.

If you make a nice zone or add neat features or good code to Duris, you
will be rewarded for your hard work and will move up the ladder. We, the
Forgers of the Realms, wish to encourage everyone to work hard and
contribute to the never-ending growth of our world.

We need your help!

With that said: if you work for us, you WILL be rewarded. On the other
hand, NO ONE will receive a god just because they are friends ith the
bosses or some other such garbage. We do NOT give away free gods or god
levels. Giving these away would undermine the entire principle of
participation and it would be entirely unfair to those who have worked hard
to get where they are. If you don't get the god of your choice, and want to
be higher, more work is probably the answer.

If, however, you feel you have been cheated, you may request an audience
with an Overlord, where you can voice your concerns and have them heard.
This will hopefully resolve any problems.
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, AT"
===========================================================================
"At" lets you perform a command as though you were in a different location.

Examples:
        at fizzwig shout touch me
        at 1201 lick trout
        at lamp look
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, CHEATING"
===========================================================================
This is a sensitive issue on any MUD. Cheating degrades the environment and
can do considerable damage to a MUD's reputation when it occurs.

Thus, on Duris, we have developed a very strict policy toward cheating, and
you MUST understand it. This policy is simple and to the point:

     If you are caught cheating with your god, you will be deleted
     from the MUD. You will lose all of your god powers and there
     will be no questions asked and no second chances.

There are no exceptions. This rulings stands for Forgers as well as all
other gods. Cheating is NOT tolerated here. We have adopted this strict
policy in order to discourage people from cheating in the first place. Just
don't do it, it's not worth the consequences if you are caught.

And, as a reminder, Duris has VERY detailed logs. Almost everything you d 
as a god is logged: loading objects, dropping things, moving about, almost
everything.

We are not trying to be policemen here, nor Big Brother. Always watching
over your shoulder waiting for you to make the wrong move. Trust is a major
factor that affects all of us gods, and without it, we would never gain any
major accomplishments. The Forgers almost never look at the logs, but they
do, occasionally, when they are bored or receive a complaint. Don't be
nervous about having your actions recorded; just don't cheat. If, by
chance, someone witnesses you cheating (as is most often the case), you are
history, period.

If you have even the remotest doubt as to whether your actions would
constitute cheating, DON'T DO IT. Put the situation on hold and consult
with a higher level god.

Thus, the policy is set. You have read it and are expected to abide by it.
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, CLONE"
===========================================================================
Syntax:  clone <mob|obj> <name> <count>

This lets you clone a given mob or object <count> times, which is useful
for avoiding wizlog spam.
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, DEBUG"
===========================================================================
Syntax: debug

This command toggles debug mode on and off. Debug mode logs the last 100
commands by ALL player characters, as well as the location of all players.
Current default is on.
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, DEMOTE"
===========================================================================
Demote a player to level 1. It also rerolls all of the player's attributes,
&+mas well as clears out all skills learned by the player.

Example: demote fizzwig
===========================================================================
See also: "GOD, ADVANCE"

#
"GOD, ECHO"
===========================================================================
"Echo" will send a message to the room which will display to all players in
the room, regardless of their state of consciousness.

Example: echo This is a test.
         will show to others as
         This is a test.
===========================================================================
See also: "GOD, GSHOUT", "GOD, ECHOA", "GOD, ECHOZ"

#
"GOD, ECHOA"
===========================================================================
"Echoa" will globally send a typed message to ALL players, regardless of
their current state of consciousness (sleeping, etc.).

Example: echoa LET THE QUEST BEGIN
         will display to everyone (besides you) as
         LET THE QUEST BEGIN
===========================================================================
See also: "GOD, GSHOUT", "GOD, ECHO", "GOD, ECHOZ"

#
"GOD, ECHOZ"
===========================================================================
&+m"Echoz" is similar to "echo" except the message is echoed within the zone&n
&+monly.&n

&+mExample: echoz Touch my monkey.&n
&+m         will be seen as:&n
&+m         Touch my monkey.&n
===========================================================================
See also: "GOD, GSHOUT", "GOD, ECHO", "GOD, ECHOA"

#
"GOD, FINGER"
===========================================================================
&+mSyntax: finger <player>&n

&+mThis gives you a player's name, title, level, class, race, and the last&n
&+mtime they saved.&n
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, FORCE"
===========================================================================
&+mSyntax:  force <victim> <argument>&n

&+mThis causes the game to react as if the victim had entered <argument>.&n
&+mExcessive forcing is frowned upon.&n
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, FREEZE"
===========================================================================
&+mSyntax:  freeze <victim>&n

&+mThe mud will accept no commands from the victim until you freeze them&n
&+magain, toggling it off. This is a very effective command, and should be&n
&+mused sparingly.&n
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, GOTO"
===========================================================================
&+m"Goto" lets you change your location to the target's location.&n

&+mExamples: goto 1201         -takes you to room 1201&n
&+m          goto poofbrain    -takes you to Poofbrain&n
&+m          goto lamp         -takes you to the top lamp in the database&n
===========================================================================
See also: "GOD, TELEPORT", "GOD, TRANS"

#
"GOD, GRANT" "GOD, REVOKE"
===========================================================================
Syntax:  grant <player> <command>&n

"Grant" lets you grant a player a command normally above their level, until
someone uses "revoke" to remove the ability. Be VERY careful in its usage.
The grantable commands form a limited subset of god commands. You can only
revoke a command that was previously granted.
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, GSHOUT"
===========================================================================
&+mThis command is like "shout," but it rings out across the world.&n

&+mExample: gshout I'm the greatest in the universe.&n
&+m         will appear to most people as&n
&+m         Bippy shouts from the heavens 'I'm the greatest in the universe.'&n
===========================================================================
See also: SHOUT

#
"GOD, INGAME"
===========================================================================
&+mIngame" is the same as inroom, except it affects the entire mud instead of&n
&+monly 1 room.&n
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, INROOM"
===========================================================================
&+m"Inroom" lets you affect an entire room with a command that normally would&n
&+monly affect one person.&n

&+m<string> should contain 1 occurrence of ONE of the following:&n

&+m    %p -all players in the room&n
&+m    %m -all mobs in the room&n
&+m    %a -both mobs and players in the room&n

&+mExample: inroom teleport %p 19617 (Teleports everyone in the room to room&n
&+m19617).&n
&+mExample: inroom force %m report (Forces all mobs in the room to report).&n
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, KNOWLEDGE"
===========================================================================
&+mMortals on any MUD can often get lost or have problems that are far beyond&n
&+mtheir control. This generally occurs no matter how well-coded a MUD is.&n

&+mThus there WILL be situations where you are the only god around and a&n
&+mproblem will arise. It is your responsibility as a god to know the MUD, its&n
&+mpolicies, and its general workings, so that you might be able to help out&n
&+mwhen something goes wrong. If you encounter a problem that you feel only a&n
&+mhigher god or Forger can handle, refer the problem up the ladder. There is&n
&+mnothing wrong with doing that, nor is it a bad thing to do. Actually, if&n
&+myou are in doubt as to the wisdom of your decision, it is often more&n
&+madvantageous to do this than make an incorrect ruling.&n

&+mHowever, we don't want a bunch of gods running around who know nothing&n
&+mabout the mud, and who can't answer simple questions that a mortal might&n
&+mask. If you don't feel knowledgeable enough about things, try to learn so&n
&+myou will be ready.&n

&+mRemember, you represent our entire MUD when you talk one-on-one with a&n
&+mmortal. You are the god, and your actions will reflect heavily upon us all.&n
&+mOne god who m kes a dumb mistake with a wrong person could spell disaster.&n
&+mBad publicity on the Internet and in the Usenet newsgroups would be very&n
&+mdamaging, not to mention embarrassing.&n

&+mSo, in synopsis, if there is a problem beyond your control, don't blow 'em&n
&+moff. Get help.&n
===========================================================================

#
"GOD, LEVELS"
===========================================================================
&+mSyntax: levels [<class>]&n

&+mThis command gives you a list of each experience level for a given class,&n
&+mor those of your own class with no argument. Do not give this information&n
&+mto mortals, as we are trying to hide numbers from the game.&n
===========================================================================

