#
"GROUP RECALL" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <group>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Teleportation

The caster and his entire group will instantly be transported back to the 
place the caster is "homed" at. The caster must be grouped last or everyone 
grouped after him will be left behind. They must also be strong of will and 
body to effectively transport their fellow members through the mists of 
magic to safety.

&+RWARNING&n:If the caster is overburdened they may leave some items
        behind at the spot where the spell was cast.
===========================================================================
See also: "WORD OF RECALL", HOME

#
"GROUP STORNOGS SPHERES" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     N/A
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster or until dispelled
Type of spell:  Protection

"Group stornogs spheres" brings into existence a series of orange that 
rotate around the caster as well as anyone grouped with him.  These spheres 
absorb magical energies directed at anyone protected by them, leaving those
protected unharmed.  The amount of energy the spheres can absorb depends on
the casters' level.  
===========================================================================
See also: "STORNOGS SPHERES"

#
GROW (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <room>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Summoning

"Grow" allows the Druid to create forest in non-forest areas. Depending on 
the terrain, it takes different amounts of time for the forest to grow. 
In order to for this to work, you must have solid ground on which to the
forest. Desert, water, mountains and indoor areas cannot be utilized.
===========================================================================
See also: TERRAIN, COMMUNE

#
GSAY (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         gsay <message>

This is a "conference" mode of communication used by grouped players. Only 
the members of your group will hear your communication and it also works 
when group members are not in the same room.

Example:
   gsay Let's kill this wraith.

Note: Gsay may possibly be eavesdropped on by classes with the skill 
      "listen".
===========================================================================
See also: GROUP, SAY, SHOUT, LISTEN

#
GUARD (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         guard <name>

When guarding a person, there is a chance that you may jump in front of
them protect them from being attacked.
===========================================================================
See also: DEFEND, RESCUE

#
GUARDIAN (Specialization)
===========================================================================
As their name suggests, the Guardian is a true savior to all. They are 
able to dive in and often rescue their entire group in the heat of battle. 
They can also use their shield as a weapon to cause extra damage by Shield 
Punching their opponent, then following up with extended riposte abilities.

Skills
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
31st level:     Follow-Up Riposte
46th level:     Shield Punch
51st level:     Rescue All

===========================================================================
See also: RESCUE, "SHIELD PUNCH", "FOLLOW-UP RIPOSTE", "RESCUE ALL"  

#
GUILD GUILDS ASSOCIATIONS CLANS (General Information)
===========================================================================
This document is designed to answer any questions regarding the creation
of player guilds on Duris. Under the current guild system players are
responsible for the organization of their own guilds. 
The gods themselves will not be responsible or serve any function in the
running of a guild.

How To Begin A Guild
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

a) The requirements for forming a guild are as follows :
    -All guild members must be at least 25th level or above. The level
      requirement is simply to ensure that the people in the guild are
      familiar with Duris and how it's run.
    -A guild may have upto, but no more than, 3 shared characters.
      These characters can be accessable by some/all members of the guild,
      but are not directly owned by anybody in the guild.
    -Guilds must also keep a member count of at least 5 members, 
      this 5 does &+RNOT&n include the 3 shared characters.  The guild is
      also limited to a maximum of 35 members in the guild at a time.
    -A one time fee of 1,000 platinum is required to start the guild.
      This not does include a guildhall.

IMPORTANT
    -You may only have one character in a guild, and at most one alt in the
      &+RSAME GUILD&n, at a time.  No exceptions.
    -You as a player can only secede from three different guilds EVER.
      If you leave your third different guild, that's it.
    -If you leave a guild you must wait one real week before joining
      another.
    -You may only kick out one member per mud month at a time.

b) What this allows -Once this happens the guild will be created and the
   person forming the guild will be flagged as a guild 'leader'. This will
   allow him/her to recruit members into the guild and promote/demote them
   accordingly. This is done completely without god interference and
   controlled by the code. Any new members will be automatically be flagged
   and titled as a member of the guild. This also will create a guild bank
   account which is accessible by Leaders and Deputies.
   Once a guild has been started and approved by Duris, the guild members
   of that guild must run their own activities. How many people there are
   of a certain guild rank is entirely up to the players. The gods
   themselves will have no interference with the running of the guild
   themselves. Any new members, once enrolled will automatically be titled
   as a basic member of that guild.

Guild Structure
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Guilds have specific ranks within them which give their members to ability
do different things depending on their rank. How this works is as follows :

Leader -A leader can change the names of all the ranks (this allows an
guild of sorcerers to name the leader as "ArchMage" rather than "Leader".
These titles must be realistic in a &+Yfantasy world&n. A leader also has the
ability to flag a player as an enemy to the guild (leaders are the only
ones that can remove this flag as well). The leader can also add on an
'on parole' flag to members.

Deputy -A deputy (or higher) can delete, promote and demote members and
also has access to withdraw money from the guild's bank account.

Officer -An officer (or higher) has the right to fine lower members
(dealing out punishments etc).

Senior member -A senior member (or higher) has the right to enroll new
members.

Normal member -A Normal member just has general abilities, access to any
guildhalls that might be available etc. They can also see what other guild
members are online.

Enemy -The guild leader has the ability to flag a member as a guild enemy
as well. This will cause the guild npc's (if any) to attack the player on
sight and is used for betrayal etc.

Applying for Membership
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
In order to be allowed into a guild the player must first apply himself as
an applicant. You can do this by using the 'Society Apply <member>' command
where <member> is the enrolling member of the guild you wish to join.

Guild Locker
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
All guilds currently have a guild locker.  Go to any bank in a hometown
where you can access your personal locker, and you can access your guild
locker with &+Yenter locker guild&n.  All members share access to this
locker.  This replaces the need for guild chests in guildhalls.

===========================================================================
See also: CONSTRUCT, SOCIETY, GUILDHALL, TITLE

#
GUILDHALLS (General Information)
===========================================================================
After you start a guild you will most likely want to start saving money to
start building your guild somewhere to hang out and organize your next
adventuring trip. For this purpose you can build your guild a guildhall.
The cost involved in building your guildhall are as follows:

        Golem (Sorc, Cleric, Warrior)            10,000 platinum
        Shopkeeper &+RDISABLED&n                      10,000 platinum
        Inn &+RDISABLED&n                             5,000 platinum
        Fountain                                 500 platinum
        Holy/Unholy Fountain                     3,000 platinum
        Magic Mouth &+RDISABLED&n                     500 platinum
        Healing Room                             3,000 platinum
        Chest &+RDISABLED&n                           5,000 platinum
        Guildhall Rooms                          1,000 platinum
        Portals                                  20,000 platinum

For further information on how to construct your guildhall and these items
within your guildhalls, read the details in the construct section.

===========================================================================
See also: CONSTRUCT, GUILD, SOCIETY, SACK

#
"HALF ELF" HALF-ELF (General Information)
===========================================================================
Half-elves are shunned by humans on this world, and, because of this, are
limited in the classes in which they may train. They do have, however, the
option of starting in one of several cities. Half-elves have infravision
and live much longer than humans, although not as long as their full-
blooded grey elf kin.

Classes:    Warrior, Conjurer, Sorcerer, Ranger, Druid, Bard, Assassin,
            Cleric, Paladin, Necromancer, Thief.
Statistics: Half-elves tend to be slightly weaker and frailer than humans,
            but also tend to be slightly quicker and smarter. Also better
            looking.
Innates:    Infravision.

===========================================================================
See also: RACES, HUMAN, "GREY ELF", INNATE, INFRAVISION

#
HALFLING (General Information)
===========================================================================
Halflings are remarkably small humanoids that are renowned for being
goodhearted and naive. Customarily thieves by nature, halflings are much
weaker than humans, but possess impressive dexterity and often have a
penchant towards meticulousness. Unfortunately for other beings who must
deal with them, they also have a tendency toward kleptomania. They also
possess infravision. They are the smallest of the races, and often
overlooked.

Classes:    Warrior, Cleric, Shaman, Sorcerer, Thief, Mercenary, Bard &
            Illusionist.
Statistics: Halflings have absolutely amazing dexterity, and tend to be
            fast on their feet as well, they are however, much weaker than
            humans, and tend not to be as smart or wise either. They are
            'cute' though, so no one tends to notice.
Innates:    Infravision 

===========================================================================
See also: RACES, INNATE, INFRAVISION, STEAL

