#
"HAMMER MASTERY" (Skill)
===========================================================================
The Ragelord in their advance studies and training have developed an 
affinity in their weapon skills to the use of a Hammer. Whilst wielding 
their weapon of preference they naturally gain a better precision and 
accuracy in their melee strikes.
===========================================================================
See also: RAGELORD, "HAMMER MASTERY", BERSERKER, SKILL_BERSERKER

#
HAMSTRING (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         Hamstring <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes

A very very high level rogue can hamstring his victims. He slices at his
victim's hamstrings, greatly impairing their ability to run away. If the
rogue successfully hamstrings his victim, the rogue can much more easily
stab the poor guy to death.
===========================================================================

#
"HAND OF DEATH" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

"Hand of Death" brings the soul of the undead back to the corpse and 
reanimates it to 'life' once again. This restores most of the experience
lost by the death.
===========================================================================
See also: RESURRECT 

#
HARDCORE (General Information)
===========================================================================
When you create a character on Duris you have the option of creating it as
"Hardcore". These characters are enhanced in most areas such as they do
increased damage, have greater resistance to damage and have higher hp than
non-hardcore characters. Hardcore characters also do not require the
special "potions" as others do to move past level 50, they are able to
simply exp right up to level 56. However they have a limited li e-span and
will cease to exist completely upon the fifth death of the character.
===========================================================================

#
HARM (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

"Harm" will remove a great deal of lifeforce from the victim, with the
maximum amount lost being dependent on the proficiency of the caster. It is
not (quite) possible to kill using this spell.
===========================================================================
See also: "FULL HARM"

#
"HARMONIC RESONANCE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: Room
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

"Harmonic resonance" evokes a natural phenomenon which adapts itself to
the type of terrain that the spell is cast upon.  Different types of 
terrain evoke different spell-type responses from the resonance.
===========================================================================

#
HARPY GARGOYLE (General Information)
===========================================================================
Harpies are a race of bird people that come from the jungle climates of 
Khomani-Khan. A matriarchal system governs their towns, where the females 
are usually more powerful and dangerous. They are usually frail in physical 
form, but quite adept at the mystical arts. Harpies are slender and 
humanoid, with large wings. The most vital fact of the Harpy species is 
their alliance with no single race, as they are borne into the world 
neutral. They must complete a quest to choose their destiny in the world of 
Duris. Indeed, the harpy culture breeds those who follow the path of 
darkness, light, and even undeath.

Class list:       Sorcerer, Conjurer, Ethermancer, Bard
Statistics:       Harpies are an aerial race that tend to be quick and
                  hearty, yet not very strong. They are much more suited to
                  magic than any combat classes. They regain their spell
                  slots via 'tupor', a calming-state. Due to their bird-
                  like nature, Harpies are constantly flying and have the 
                  ability to 'flutter' to avoid attack and their keen eyes 
                  can see farther than other races. Harpies cannot wear 
                  equipment on their feet or legs, yet they may wear horns.
Innate abilities: fly, perception, dayvision, ultravision
Strength:         Harpies are extremely agile and dexterous creatures with
                  hearty constitutions.
Weakness:         Harpies are usually considerably more frail than an
                  average human, though slightly stronger than elvenkind.
                  Due to their communion with the forces of wind and cold,
                  Harpies must be at least resting or even asleep in order
                  to tupor, thereby making them extremely prone to attack.
                  
===========================================================================
See also: RACES, FLY, PERCEPTION, DAYVISION, TUPOR, FLUTTER, ULTRAVISION, 
          INNATE

#
HASTE (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

"Haste" grants the victim a faster pulse speed, allowing them to hit more 
often than without it. It also adds an archery hit, allowing an archer to
hit more often. When used on casters, it allows them to cast their spell
more quickly.
===========================================================================
See also: SLOWNESS

#
HATRED (Innate)
===========================================================================
Dwarves are as changeable as the rock they came from but as a result they
also never forget. Many are the long wars fought against the invading orcs
and the battles against the duergar dwarves and drow elves. Over the 
passing millennia deep hatred has grown into the hearts of all dwarves 
and they will battle this evil anywhere and everywhere. A result of this 
hatred is a rage that will help a dwarf to keep on fighting when others 
others would tire and to fight with determination unheard of.
===========================================================================
See also: MOUNTAIN DWARF, DROW, DUERGAR

