#
"HEAVEN" "HELL" (General Information)
===========================================================================
When you die to another player you will be placed in your respective
heaven. Each side of the racewars has their own heaven. The only way to
leave heaven is by resurrection, or by waiting a specific amount of time. 
Depending on how high level you are, that will determine the length of time
your mortal soul binds to a new body. You will only visit your heaven when 
you die to another player. Without the limitations of a body your mind is
more attune to magic and you will be able to memorize any spell you are
able to use.
===========================================================================
See also: DEATH, PKILL

#
"HELLFIRE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: Caster
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     n/a
Duration:       Dependant on level of caster
Type of spell:  Protection

"Hellfire" opens a channel from the bowels of hell unto the antipaladin
himself. Imbued with the power of pure hellborne fire, the antipaladin not
only has a more acute vampiric touch, but his touch extends through to the
tip of his weapon. In other words, he can vamp while wielding and the vamp 
is based only on the dice of that weapon.
===========================================================================
See also: "VAMPIRIC TOUCH"

#
HELLSPAWN (Specialization)
===========================================================================
A dealer of death, the Hellspawn is able to instinctively detect the target 
with the least vital energies remaining. Should they receive the killing 
blow, there is the possibility to "Spawn" a creature of Undead from the 
fresh corpse.

