#
HOME (General Information)
===========================================================================
Your home is the place you respawn after dying and is set by default to
your starting hometown. In order to change your home, you must have 50
platinum in your possession and type 'home' in a hometown.
===========================================================================
See also: SOCIETY, GUILD, GUILDHALL

#
HOMETOWN HOMETOWNS
===========================================================================
A "hometown" is a city of a particular race of Duris. There are numerous
hometowns across the land, and you will start in your race's birth 
hometown when you enter the game. When you die, you will respawn in the
city of your birth, unless you have paid to reset your home to another 
place (see help home). 

Some of these Hometowns include:

   -Tharnadia, the Birthplace of Humans
   -Charing, City of Elves

===========================================================================
See also: HOME, THARNADIA, CHARING

#
HUMAN (General Information
===========================================================================
The human race encompasses the general population of civilized towns
and cities.  They are commonplace beings, and are found in most
populated areas.  Humans have the broadest range of classes from which
to choose, but no extraordinary innate abilities.

Class list:       Warrior, Ranger, Paladin, Cleric, Druid, Sorcerer,
                  Necromancer, Conjurer, Thief
, Assassin, Mercenary,
                  Bard, Monk, Alchemist, Illusionist, Shaman.
Statistics:       Humans are the baseline against which all other races are
                  compared, as a result, they have no strengths or
                  weaknesses.
Innate abilities: None

===========================================================================
See also: RACES, INNATE

#
HUNTSMAN (Specialization)
===========================================================================
Specialized at scouting enemies, the Huntsman has learned to stalk their 
victims unnoticed, hide in the surroundings and set up traps warning them 
about trespassing enemies.

Skills
