#
IDLE (General Information)
===========================================================================
The term "Idle" is used to classify when your character is logged on but no 
commands are being entered. After you are idle for 10 minutes, you will 
automatically enter the "Void". After 15 minutes of idle time, you will 
"Idle Rent". Your character will exit the game at whatever location he/she
is currently at. When you re-enter the game, you will start at whatever
place you were last at. This also holds true for characters who are or are 
not link-dead.  
===========================================================================
See also: RENT, VOID, LINK

#
IGNORE (General Information)
===========================================================================
Syntax:  ignore <victim>

Used to ignore communications and social actions from a single devious or
annoying person.  To stop ignoring anyone, simply type "ignore."
===========================================================================

#
"ILLUSIONARY WALL" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: direction
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster 
Type of spell:  Illusion

This spell creates an illusion that effectively hides normal exits from
the naked eye. Anyone attempting to try and exit in the direction that this 
wall exists has a chance to disbelieve the illusion and pass. One can also
try to search the area around where the exit once was and may find the wall
thus negating the effects. 
===========================================================================

#
ILLUSIONIST (Sub-Class of: Magic-User)
===========================================================================
Illusionist are the magical masters of the unreal and the shadow. They
are capable of illusions so powerful no one can help but believe they are 
real. They are also masters of deception and many have foolishly let them
into their ranks, to their doom. Illusionist tend to be highly intelligent 
and use this to their advantage. 

Allowable races:        Human, Gnome, Halfling, Goblin, Orc, Phantom, Lich. 
Equipment usage:        Like all classes on Duris, Illusionist have their 
			own specific item restrictions.  They have a
                        very small range of weapons they can use and a
                        small range of armor to choose from. They have 
                        very little restrictions on what miscellaneous 
                        magical items they can use, though.      
             
===========================================================================
See also: MAGIC, SKILL_ILLUSIONIST

#
IMMOLATE (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect:	<victim>
Aggressive: 	Yes
Cumulative:	Yes
Duration: 	Varies
Type of Spell: 	Fire

A conflagration of fire is sent towards the victim, burning their flesh
from one to five rounds. 
===========================================================================

#
IMMORTALS GODS (General Information)
===========================================================================
Gods are people who have obtained level 57 or above. They should be
respected for having met and overcome the challenges of Duris DikuMUD.
However, there are certain rules by which they must abide:

1. They must not interfere with or hinder mortals.
2. Immortals cannot give out information such as: statistics of a player,
   statistics of items or other private information.
3. They cannot kill mortals. 
4. Immortals cannot give away objects or equipment.
5. They must not use their immortal to gather information later used on
   their mortal.
6. Breaking any of these rules will subject the immortal to immediate
   demotion.

Nobody likes rules, but we need them to keep the game fun and interesting.
===========================================================================
See also: RULES, PETITION, CREDITS, WIZLIST

#
"IMPRISONMENT" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster 
Type of spell:  Fear

This powerful spell creates an illusionary wall around the victim. While 
the victim is encased in this wall he or she cannot attack anyone nor can 
any physical or magical damage befall them. The only way a victim can free 
themselves is by trying to move about or by someone trying to attack 
them while imprisoned. If the victim issues no commands and nobody tries
to attack them they will be imprisoned for a very long time. It is 
important to note that due to the difficult nature of this spell it requires 
that both the caster and victim not be physically engaged in combat. 

HINT for Victims: If you are caught in this spell your best bet is to just 
spam any direction until you are free, other commands work as well so you 
can experiment if you like. Once you start trying to break free you will be 
out in 2 to 4 rounds of combat in many cases.

HINT for Illusionists: If your having a hard time getting a victim out of 
combat so you can cast this spell try using your Stunning Visions spell, 
if your lucky it will hit and you should have time to imprison your 
victim before they engage anyone in combat. 
===========================================================================

#
"IMPROVED HEAL" (Innate)
===========================================================================
This skill improves the power of all healing spells. This is a passive
innate and is always active.
===========================================================================
