#
INFRAVISION (Spell)
===========================================================================
Infravision is the ability to sense the presence of creatures in a dark
room by the means of heat.

This can be a spell or an innate ability.
===========================================================================
See also: INNATE, ULTRAVISION

#
INGREDIENTS (General Information)
===========================================================================
Various "Ingredients" are located throughout the world, buried under the 
ground. Herbs, Garlic, Nightshade, Mandrake Roots and Dragon's Blood are
just a few of the many ingredients that exist. Alchemists require stock-
piles of these ingredients in order to "Mix" their potions. Whereas, 
Forest Druids only require Herbs. You can gather ingredients via the
"Forage" command.
===========================================================================
See also: ALCHEMIST, "FOREST DRUID", MIX, FORAGE

#
INNATE (General Information)
===========================================================================
Typing "innate", gives you a list of your race's or classes' innate 
abilities, if any. Innate abilities are those skills or spells which all 
members of your race or class know instinctively. To use an innate ability, 
use the proper syntax for the given skill or spell. To get more information 
on a particular skill or spell, type "help <skill>" or "help <spell>," 
respectively. The innate abilities for each race or class are listed under 
their help entry.
===========================================================================
See also: RACES, CLASSES

#
INNS (General Information)
===========================================================================
Inns are places located throughout the world that are used to store your 
gathered equipment while you are not playing the game. If you wish to quit 
the game and not lose any of your gear, you must "rent" a room at an inn or 
camp.
===========================================================================
See also: RENT, CAMP, QUIT

#
"INSECTS" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

When cast, "Insects" creates up to four poisonous illusionary swarms of 
insects out of thin air that attacks the victim. The illusion will end when 
the victim dies or leaves the area for a time and if the caster dies or the 
duration of the spell ends. The illusion will also end after it has taken
enough damage. Any victim of the poisoning will continue  to be poisoned 
until it wears off or is neutralized.
===========================================================================

#
"INSTANT KILL" (Skill)
===========================================================================
As the name implies, "instant kill" provides the character with a very
minuscule chance of killing a player or mob instantly, upon the application
of a successful backstab.
===========================================================================
See also: BACKSTAB, SKILL_ASSASSIN

#
INSTRUMENT INSTRUMENTS MUSIC (General Information)
===========================================================================
Instruments are a necessity of a bard and needed to create magical affects.
The bard must first be holding the appropriate instrument and then type
'play <songname>'.  The various instruments are as follows:  flute, harp,
horn, drums, lyre, mandolin.  Unlike spells, the music played by a bard 
is continuous when the bard begins playing and will continue until he/she
ends the song or begins a new song.  Songs do eventually end, of course. 
===========================================================================
See also: PLAY, SONGS, BARD, SKILL_BARD, PIPER, SKILL_PIPER

#
"INTELLECT FORTRESS" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <caster>
Aggressive:     N/A
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       1 day
Type of Spell:  Enchantment

"Intellect Fortress" fortifies the mind of the caster with a superior
intelligence. This spell helps reduce the effects of mental attacks.
===========================================================================

#
INTELLIGENCE (General Information)
===========================================================================
Intelligence is a measure of quickness and accuracy of thought, basically, 
how well you can think. Intelligence is the primary attribute for Mages and 
is certainly useful for all others as well.
===========================================================================
See also: STATISTICS

#
INVENTORY
===========================================================================
This command allows you to see what you are currently carrying. It will not
show you items that are stored inside containers, nor undetectable items
(invisible items, for example).
===========================================================================
See also: EQUIPMENT

