Area of effect: <room>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Summoning

This spell causes a bright torch-like light to appear over the casters'
head, illuminating the entire room. The light travels with the caster until 
its duration expires.
===========================================================================

#
MAGIC (General Information)
===========================================================================
Magic is the broad category of phenomena that goes above and beyond normal
mortal powers. This can range from spells with an immensely wide variety
of effects to the uncanny abilities of a particular type of creature to the
curative powers of a potion to the power of song, and even further, into
areas as yet unexplored. Magic permeates the Realms, binding it together,
but few mortals can claim to possess a working knowledge of the Art, let
alone so-called "mastery."

A list of major topics discussing magic can be found under "help mystics".
===========================================================================
See also: MYSTICS

#
"MAGIC MISSILE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim> | <victim> <direction>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

Casting this spell will cause a burst of magical bolts to spray forth from
the caster's fingertips, impacting on the target with deadly accuracy.
Between one and five missiles will be fired, depending on the proficiency
of the caster.
===========================================================================

#
"MAGIC-USER" "MAGIC USER" MAGE (General Information)
===========================================================================
The term "Magic-User" defines a class of individuals who spend their lives
training in the use of arcane magical spellcraft. They are the ones who
stand at the back of a party during battle and hurl powerful offensive
spells at the enemy. Because they are so powerful in their discipline, they
are typically the most frail in stature.

There are subclasses of Magic-User, each with their own specialties:
Sorcerers, Necromancers and Conjurer classes that are very specific to 
Magic-Users. Being part of the larger class-group, these classes are 
affected by the same class restrictions on equipment and are similar in 
to-hit rolls and average hit points. There are also some other classes that 
only loosely fall within the "Magic-User" definition, these are: 
Psionicists, Illusionists and Alchemists. These sub-classes tend to have similar 
resistances and susceptibilities to things like spells, paralysis, dragon 
breath, etc. Each sub-class rises in level according to its own experience 
chart.

NOTE: Use "help <classname>" for information on each of the sub-classes.
===========================================================================
See also: SORCERER, NECROMANCER, CONJURER, PSIONICIST, ILLUSIONIST,
          ALCHEMIST

#
MAGICIAN
===========================================================================
   - Skill: Expeditious retreat: improved retreat in any direction, even
      when tanking
   - Spell (10th): obscuring mist: when cast, the room the illusionist is 
      in becomes no-scan
   - Spell (11th): supress sound: when cast, the illusionist silences his own
      group, allowing them to not make any noise when walking
   - Innate: Improved Flee: when the illusionist flees, it appears that he
      flees in several directions
===========================================================================
See Also: ILLUSIONIST, SKILL_ILLUSIONIST

