#
MEDITATE (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         meditate (while resting)

"Meditate" allows the player to memorize/pray for spells with a chance of
halving the time. A single proficiency check is made at the half way point
for each spell. If successful, the spell will be memorized/prayed for at
that time. If unsuccessful, the spell will take the normal time before it
is memorized/prayed. Because meditate is the focusing of the mind, most
actions will stop the meditation.
===========================================================================
See also: PRAY, MEMORIZE

#
MEMORIZE PRAY FORGET (General Information)
===========================================================================
Syntax:  memorize | pray (while resting)
         memorize <spellname> | pray <spellname> (while resting)
         forget <spellname>

"Memorize" and "Pray" let you put a spell in your active repertoire. To 
successfully memorize or pray for a spell, you must be holding or have in 
your inventory the appropriate item, dependent on your class. Magic-User 
subclasses must have a spellbook which contains the scribed spell to 
successfully memorize it.

Memorizing or praying without specifying a spellname allows you to
resume your studies/prayers and lists the time remaining to complete
each spell.

"Forget" lets you purge a spell from your active repertoire.
===========================================================================
See also: CAST, PRACTICE, MEDITATE, "SPELL SLOT"

#
"MEMORY BLOCK" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect:	<victim>
Aggressive:	Yes
Cumulative:	N/A

"Memory block" causes the victim to forget how to cast, purging the
memory of spells from the victim's mind.
===========================================================================

