#
NAMES (General Information)
===========================================================================
This is a medieval based fantasy mud, if you pick a name that is NOT suited
to a mud of that theme, you will be asked to change it. Common names like
Bob, Tomas, Mike are not acceptable, nor are names of famous fictional
characters such as Conan, Drizzt, Elric etc. Names comprised of compound
words (2 words joined into one) or names that sound like titles
(Darkknight, Swordmaster, Deathbringer, etc.) will also not be accepted.
Obviously stupid names will not be accepted. If you get one by when noone
is available to review you, expect to be forced to change it. Profane names
will result in deletion.
===========================================================================

#
"NATURES TOUCH" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:      No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Healing

This spell allows the Druid to call on the healing power of nature to 
restore the victim's life-force. It is terrain based (heals more in forests, 
less inside) and increases healing power with levels.
===========================================================================
See also: TERRAIN

#
NCHAT
===========================================================================
Syntax:        nchat hi there

This is a communications channel for new players to the game to talk to
others on their own racewar side at lower levels. It can also be used as a
means to gain information and help in regard to the game. 

This channel will remain open to you only until you reach a certain level.
However there will be a set of higher level, more experienced players
within the game that have special access to this channel who will provide 
assistance and help where they are able. 
===========================================================================
See also: NEWBIE, TOGGLE_NCHAT

#
NECROLYTE (Specialization)
===========================================================================
The Necrolyte possesses heightened senses capable of detecting the dead. He
is a master in the use of staves and can summon the very shadows to serve
him.

Skills
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
31st level:     Staff Mastery

Innate Ability
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
30th level:     Vision of the Dead

Spells
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
4th circle:     Darkness
9th circle:     Raise Shadow

===========================================================================
See also: NECROMANCER, "VISION OF THE DEAD", DARKNESS, "RAISE SHADOW", "STAFF MASTERY"

#
NECROMANCER (Sub-Class of: Magic-User)
===========================================================================
Necromancers are the branch of magic-users devoted to spells dealing with
the dead and undead. The spells available to a Necromancer are primarily
offensive in nature and are not granted by a deity. In fact, many of a
Necromancer's spells are viewed as evil by the gods. However, the
Necromancer's dark art can transcend the boundary between life and death,
and harness the energies of those on both sides.

Allowable races:        Human, Half-Elf, Drow, Orc, Goblin, Githyanki,
                        Lich, Vampire
Innate abilities:       No class-specific innate abilities.
Equipment usage:        Necromancers have their own classification of item
			restriction. They have a small range of weapons
			that they can wield and a smaller range of armor to
			choose from. They can, however, use most magical
			items.
			
===========================================================================
See also: SKILL_NECROMANCER

