"NONEXISTENCE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: Room
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

This spell when cast causes everything in the room to turn invisible and 
all players/mobs in room to be hidden from site. Once anyone effected by 
this spell moves they will no longer be hidden but will remain invisible. 
===========================================================================
See also: INVISIBILITY, HIDE, VANISH

#
NOVA (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <room>	
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Summoning

"Nova" coalesces a focal point of energy comprised of pure sunlight. The
focal point grows, and grows, and grows, sucking all ambient light from
around it. This nexus of light swells until it explodes, inflicting
gruesome damage to anyone unlucky enough to be near it.
===========================================================================

#
NPC "NON PLAYER CHARACTER" (General Information)
===========================================================================
NPC is short for "non player character" and usually refers to a monster or
mobile in the game that is not controlled by an actual person. These are
the mobs created by zone makers or immortals to fill Duris for purposes
such as experience, equipment, quests, and other things.
===========================================================================
See also: PC, MOBILE, EXPERIENCE, EQUIPMENT

#
OFFENSE (Skill)
===========================================================================
This wide-ranged skill affects all areas of attack, including likelihood of
hitting your opponent, THAC0, etc. Damage without proficiency in
offense skill will be significantly lower than with it.
===========================================================================
See also: SKILLS, THAC0

#
OGRE (General Information)
===========================================================================
Ogres are a race of massive humanoids that are typically three feet taller
and twice as strong as average humans. Although they are extremely
unintelligent and clumsy, ogres are fearsome warriors and are feared by all
races. Ogres are evil and ill-tempered creatures, and they tend to be
excessively destructive and have been known to occasionally eat humans.
They live amongst themselves in clan-fashion and often organize war parties
to raid and pillage.  

Class list:        Warrior, Shaman.
Stats:             Big as house, strong as ox, ugly as sin, not quick, oh
                   and did I mention some rocks are smarter? Ogre shamans
                   have a rough time.
Innate Abilities:  doorbash, ultravision, bodyslam, bearhug, ogreroar

&+RWarning:&n As one of the eight evil races on Duris, ogres are extremely
difficult to play and face many hardships. Their hometown has been
specifically designed to make life hell, and death waits around every
corner. Ogres will most certainly encounter situations that would be deemed
"unfair" to any of the surface races. We did this to create a new challenge
for those advanced players who have "beaten" the challenge of life on the
surface world, and are looking for something more difficult. You should NOT
play an ogre unless you are a *very* advanced player and are used to the
Duris style of MUDding, or are willing to face the hardships without
complaint, as it is NOT easy.
===========================================================================
See also: RACES, INNATE, DOORBASH, INFRAVISION, BODYSLAM

#
OGREROAR
===========================================================================
     Syntax:	ogreroar <victim>
===========================================================================

#
OPEN CLOSE LOCK UNLOCK
===========================================================================
Syntax (example):
  > open door
or
  > open red (if the door is red and there is more than one to choose from)
or
  > open door south (to open the door in a particular direction)

Similar syntax applies for "close," "lock," and "unlock."
===========================================================================
See also: EXAMINE, LOOK, SEARCH

#
ORC
===========================================================================
Orcs are a race of evil humanoids that are, typically, five feet tall with
green or yellowish skin and red eyes. Orcs tend to be more social then most
other evil races, preferring to group with as many of their fellows as
possible. Orcs, while preferring the company of other orcs, are known to
also group with Ogres and Trolls, and even Drow and Duergar from time to
time. Orcs are some of the most deadly creatures to be found on Duris.

Class list:	  Warrior, Anti-Paladin, Cleric, Shaman, Sorcerer, Reaver,
		  Necromancer, Thief, Assassin, Mercenary, Bard, Alchemist,
		  Berserker, Illusionist, Conjurer.
Statistics:       Orcs tend to be weaker then most other races, but make up
                  for that weakness by the sheer force of numbers, and 
                  their unique vision, which allows them to see in both
                  darkness and light, allowing them to be the only race on
                  all of duris to travel both the lands of light and dark.
Innate Abilities: Infravision, Ultravision, Summon Horde.

&+RWarning:&n As one of the eight evil races on Duris, orcs are
extremely difficult to play and face many hardships.  Their hometown
has been specifically designed to make life hell, and death waits
around every corner.  Orcs will most certainly encounter situations
that would be deemed "unfair" to any of the good races.  We did
this to create a new challenge for those advanced players who have
"beaten" the challenge of life on the surface world, and are looking
for something more difficult.  You should NOT play an orc unless you
are a *very* advanced player and are used to the Duris style of
MUDding, or are willing to face the hardships without complaint, as it
is NOT easy.
===========================================================================
See also: RACES, INNATE, ULTRAVISION, INFRAVISION, "SUMMON HORDE"

#
"ORDER FOLLOWERS" (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         order <petname> <command>
                order followers <command>

The "order" command is used in two seperate ways. Classes that have the 
ability to charm mobs must "order" the "pet" to do what the player wants.

Example:        order wolf kill duck

To order multiple followers use the command "order followers"

Example:        order followers kill duck

The second type of "order" command is used by players that have purchased 
a ship. For more information on how the "order" command applies to ships, 
see "help ships."
===========================================================================
See also: PETS, SHIPS

#
OUTCAST
===========================================================================
Players are outcasted from hometowns for many reasons. If you are an
outcast in a city it means you will not be "well liked" if you go there.
The guards will hunt you down and kill you. Outcasting is permanent and can
NOT be reversed. Some reasons for being outcasted are:

* Race: Some hometowns are not accepting of other races.

For example: ALL RACES except Grey Elves, Half-Elves and Centaurs are
considered invaders to Charing and will be killed on sight.
===========================================================================
See also: SCORE, RACES

# 
"OUTDOOR SNEAK" (Innate)
===========================================================================
This allows you to move silently from one place to another while outdoors. 
While sneaking, you will be able to travel without anyone taking notice of 
your arrival or departure.
===========================================================================
See also: SNEAK, UD-SNEAK, "SQUERRIKS SNEAKY WAYS"

