PERCEPTION (Innate)
===========================================================================
Due to the Harpies natural enhanced senses they are able to perceive more
than other races, giving them longer and wider views of the open terrain
on the continent surfaces.
===========================================================================
See also: INNATE, "BOUNTY HUNTER", HARPY

#
PETS (General Information)
===========================================================================
"Pets" are creatures who will permanently follow you and your orders unless 
you attack them or rent them off. You can aquire them in several different 
ways depending on what type of character you are. Some classes have the
ability to "summon" pets. Others have the ability to "charm" a mob to make
it a pet via an innate ability or a spell. One type of character can raise
the dead to create pets. Finally, some classes are forced to purchase pets 
in pet shops located throughout the world.

NOTE:     Your pet follow orders from you until you attack it, you rent or 
          it dies.
&+RWarning:&n Some pets, when left alone, will instantly attack players
        when they enter a room. So, be careful where you leave your pets!
===========================================================================
See also: FOLLOW, ORDER

#
PETITION (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         petition <text>
      
The "Petition" command allows you to send a message to all of the Gods 
currently on the MUD (if there are any).  Certain guidelines should be
followed when petitioning:

* Players (and Gods) are &+RNOT&N to use petition as their own personal
  chat channel.

* Do &+RNOT&N use petition for reporting ideas, suggestions, or complaints.

* Do &+RNOT&N use petition to inquire if a God is logged on. If the God
  does not appear on the "who" list, assume he/she is not on.

* If you have a problem, please describe it in details right away. 
  Do not force Gods to respond to any form of "anyone there" type spam.

Remember that the Gods abide by a non-interference policy. Petition should
not be used to ask questions about equipment, areas, mobs or general game 
play.

If you have a question or need help with a problem, you can either ask 
another player, post on the Duris forums or petition. To speak privately
with a God, use the "Tell" command. Or, if you discover a bug or typo on
Duris, use the "Bug" or "Typo" command. To submit your ideas, you may
implement the "Idea" command. Lastly, if you feel you just HAVE to whine,
use your guild board (if you have access to one) or use the Duris Forums.

Abuse of the petition channel will only invoke the wrath of the gods. We
expect EVERYONE to abide by this.
===========================================================================
See also: GODS, TOGGLE_PETITION, WEBSITE, FORUMS, BUG, IDEA, TYPO, TELL

#
PHANTOM
===========================================================================
Phantoms are undead beings which lurk nearly anywhere. Usually of a
solitary nature, they have been forced to band together with the other
undead beings to survive in this battle torn environment. Their form is of
an ethereal, semi-transparent nature which allows them to move through many
obstacles that would normally hinder other earthly bodies, along with
providing some magical resistance.

Class list:       Psionicist, Reaver, Illusionist, Conjurer.
Stats:            Extremely agile and dexterous.
Innate abilities: Ultravision, Shift_Astral, Shift_Prime, Phantasmal
                  Form (level 21), Fly (level 21).

===========================================================================
See also: PSIONICIST, REAVER

