Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

This spell will stun a victim with less than a certain amount of lifeforce, 
with the amount determined by the spellcaster's proficiency.
===========================================================================

#
PRACTICE (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         practice (t  see a list of spells that may be scribed)
                practice <spell> (while holding both a spellbook and quill
                                  and resting)
		practice all (this will scribe all spells into the book
			      currently held by the player if there is 
			      enough room left)

Practice is a method of scribing your spells. This is done with the help
of a teacher in the room. For this to be done, you must have a spellbook
and quill in hand and resting comfortably. You can then 'practice <spell>'
to add a spell to your spellbook. If this command is typed without any 
parameters and you are in the presence of a teacher it will show your list
of spells.  

In the past, the practice command was also used to increase your skills.
This is no longer the case on Duris, and you must use your skills in battle
to improve them or by gaining levels.
===========================================================================
See also: SCRIBE, "SPELL SYSTEM", "SPELL SLOT", "SPELL CIRCLE", CASTER, CAST, MAGIC-USER

#
PRESERVE (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <corpse>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     Yes
Duration:       Permanent
Type of spell:  Generic

This allows the caster to extend the process of decay in a corpse.
===========================================================================
See also: EMBALM, "MASS PRESERVE", CORPSE

#
PRESSURE POINT (Innate)
===========================================================================
Once the monk reaches a certain level of power he has mastered the physiology 
of the body and uses this knowledge to strike where it will be the most 
damaging. A monk that follows the 'Way of the Snake', also referred to as 
elaphidists, have further honed his technique and is capable of inflicting 
slowness, blindness, paralysis and even death.
===========================================================================
See Also: MONK, ELAPHIDIST

#
PRIEST (General Information)
===========================================================================
Priests are individuals who choose to spread the faith of their deities 
through the use of their god-given spell-like powers. The Priest classes 
are generally charged with the vast responsibility of keeping their party
alive with their healing and defensive spells. They are also competent
fighters and can hold their own should battle come their way.

There are subclasses of Priest, each with their own specialties:
clerics, warlocks, druids, shamans and ethermancers. Clerics are the 
closest to the common image of a priest: they spread gospel and pray to 
their deities. Warlocks are Undeads that are very similar to clerics, but 
have a larger repertoire of utilitarian spells. Druids are calmer folk, who 
espouse the virtues of closeness and harmony with nature. Though, they can 
be fearsome when angered. Shamans are a primitive mixture of Priest and 
Magic-User, with some of the abilities of each, but lacking the full powers 
of either. Ethermancers use elemental magic and worship the pagan god of 
storms. The common Priest grouping means the sub-classes are affected by 
the same class-wide restrictions on equipment and are similar in to-hit 
rolls and average hit points. Each sub-class has its own experience chart 
according to which they gain levels.

NOTE: Use "help <classname>" for information on each of the sub-classes.
===========================================================================
See also: CLERIC, DRUID, SHAMAN, ETHERMANCER, WARLOCK, SKILLS

#
"PRISMATIC CUBE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <room>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on color of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

"Prismatic Cube" raises walls which cover all exits of the room that the 
caster is in. Each wall has a random effect if touched, similar to that of 
the spell 'Prismatic Spray'.
===========================================================================
See also: "PRISMATIC SPRAY"

