QUAFF POTIONS
===========================================================================
Syntax:  quaff <potion>

Quaff is used to consume a (magical) potion. Because potions are magical,
they will have no effects if quaffed in a "No Magic" room.
===========================================================================
See also: MAGIC-USER 

#
QUEST
===========================================================================
General Information.

Currently quests exist on Duris in several different forms.  The first
includes quests that are built into the game.  They may be quests for
information, reward, items, spells, and other various things.  Such
quests have quest mobs in the game.  These are monster who have
information concerning the quest.  In order to obtain the information you
must ask or tell the monster some key word which will trigger a
response.  That response may be followed by more key words, etc.  A
monster or mob may require a specific item which he will reward you for
with information, rewards, or a spell.  The gods on Duris will NOT
reveal information about these mobs.  It is up to you to find them.
The second form of quest is run by the gods themselves.  It is usually a
story that they will tell and groups must be formed to solve it.  The
quests are for FUN.  The sole idea behind doing a quest is NOT a reward.
The gods have taken their own time to create something different and
exciting for the mud.  Be grateful.  Because these quests are run by the
gods, they have the power to do what they desire and that may include
changing the form of the quest.
===========================================================================

#
"QUICK CHANT" (Skill)
===========================================================================
The better you are at quickly chanting, the faster you can cast a spell. 
Note: If you are tanking, quick chant is disabled.
===========================================================================
See also: CAST, TANK, TOGGLE

#
QUIT (General Information)
===========================================================================
Just like in real life, in the game you cannot just "quit" life. Your
character must find a safe place such as an Inn or setup camp for the night. 
There are two commands your character can therefore use to leave the game -
rent (at an Inn only) and camp. If you simply close your client and leave 
your character "link dead", it will remain in the game, which is obviously 
very dangerous, as it will then leave your character defenseless from 
attack.
===========================================================================
See also: CAMP, INNS, RENT

#
RACES (General Information)
===========================================================================
Your race is defined by the path you choose to take in the Land of Duris.
Each race has its own strengths and weaknesses and your race should be 
chosen carefully. The following races are currently available on Duris 
DikuMUD:

Human, Barbarian, Drow Elf, Grey Elf, Half-Elf, Mountain Dwarf, Duergar
Dwarf, Gnome, Halfling, Ogre, Minotaur, Goblin, Swamp Troll, Thri-Kreen,
Centaur, Githyanki, Orc, Storm Giant, Vampire, Lich, Wight,
Shadow Beast, Death Knight, Phantom, Shade, Revenant, Harpy

Note: If you are new to Duris, it is recommended that you play a "goodie"
race character, as the other sides are designed much more toward highly
advanced players. The good side races are as follows: Human, Barbarian,
Grey Elf, Half-Elf, Mountain Dwarf, Gnome, Halfling, Centaur and Storm
Giant or Harpy.

For more information on each race, type "help <racename>."  This will give
you a brief description of each race, its strengths and weaknesses, the
bonus system that applies to it, and its innate abilities, if any. It will
also tell you which classes are available for that race.

For information about the general theme of Duris, with particular attention
to the division between good, evil and undead races, type "help racewars."
===========================================================================
See also: INNATE, RACEWARS, HUMAN, BARBARIAN, DROW, "GREY ELF", HALF-ELF,
          MOUNTAIN DWARF, DUERGAR, GNOME, HALFLING, OGRE, ORC,
          "SWAMP TROLL", THRI-KREEN, CENTAUR, GITHYANKI, GOBLIN, MINOTAUR,
          "STORM GIANT", VAMPIRE, LICH, WIGHT, "SHADOW BEAST",
          "DEATH KNIGHT", PHANTOM, HARPY, REVENANT, SHADE

#
RACEWARS PKILL PLAYERKILL (General Information)
===========================================================================
Duris consists of a delicately balanced  To make these wars possible, 
player-killing (aka pkill) is tolerated and even encouraged, subject to 
rules described below.

The good races consist of (Grey Elves, Mountain Dwarves, Gnomes, Halflings, 
Centaurs, Barbarians, Half-Elves and Humans). Undead races include 
(Vampires, Liches, Wights, Shadow Beasts, Death Knights, Phantoms, 
Revenants and Shades). Evil races are (Drow Elves, Duergar Dwarves, Swamp 
Trolls, Ogres, Orcs, Goblins and Githyankis). Alltogether, there are three 
neutral races in the Land of Duris, (Minotaurs, Thri-Kreens and Harpies). 
Minotaurs and Thri-Kreens may choose either the good or e il side of the
racewar when rolling a character. But, Harpies all enter the world as a
neutral race until they complete a quest to seal their fate in Duris.

These sides are at constant war with one another, in an attempt to take
over all of Duris. Each race will have its own home city and the city's
inhabitants are aggressive to the races of the other side. For example, if 
you are a Grey Elf and try to enter Archdrathos (the city of the Drow
Elves) you will be attacked on sight by the drow mobs, guardians of the 
city and possibly drow players. The same holds true for ALL cities of the 
realms.  

Outside of those cities, however, is a dangerous place. You never know who 
or what will be waiting for you on the other side of the city walls.  You
will quickly find that traveling in groups is the best way to survive. As 
to who can attack who, anyone CAN attack anyone.

Evil and Undead races will have a much harder time on Duris than the Good 
races do. Most are blind on the surface world during the day, suffering
from the pureness of daylight. Furthermore, life will be cruel and harsh on 
them. It will be substantially more difficult for ANYONE of an evil or 
undead race to make it to a high level, let alone reach the surface and 
kill anyone. As you can see, there will be plenty of ordeals for these 
races to overcome before they will have the chance to prey on others.
In addition, ANY evil-raced person on the surface will be hunted down by 
powerful good-raced PC's and killed on sight.

This is a VERY brief description of how race wars work on Duris.  The 
more intricate details will be revealed as they unfold.
===========================================================================
See also: RACES

#
RAID (General Information)
===========================================================================
If you are trying to retrieve your corpse/EQ after dying in PvP combat you
CANNOT return unless you are fully re-equipped as outlined below.

If are trying to retrieve your corpse/EQ regardless of how you died and
encounter members of the opposite race, corpses from the opposite race or
have other information that members of the opposite race is in the zone you 
CANNOT return if you die again unless you are fully re-equipped as outlined 
below.

If you engage in PvP combat, you are &+R*required*&N to be equipped in at 
least a minimal raid kit consisting of 12 items. To see if you are indeed
raidable you can use the command 'raid' and it will return a yes/no
statement. Included in PvP combat is casting spells on either friendly or 
foes while they are pvp'ing, looting corpses and scouting.

&+YPunishment for raiding without the slots required is 1 level per 
&+Ymissing slot plus the loss off all worn and looted. This applies 
&+Yto all raiders. Cheat repeatedly and it will become harsher.

                        &+WPLEASE READ THE REST:&N

      Minor created and newbie start equipment is NOT acceptable, you must
   always wear your best equipment; if your best equipment is in your corpse,
      on the ground or in your imagination then you must use your next best.   

     Scouting and spam-looting with lowbie chars (like level one giths) is
         cheesy, and it pisses off the imms ... don't piss off the imms!

   If you are outside of your GH or Hometown, these rules are in full effect.
  So if an evil wants to exp in Wemics, or do Outcast Tower for EQ, he has to
    be in full raiding gear. If a goodie wants to exp in Smokeveil, the same
    applies as well as any other normal experience/zone/raid situation. The
      ONLY times you may bypass this are if your storage is in a different
      location than your pop spot (i.e. you pop in Ugta, your storage is in
    Tharnadia) or you are zoning to get equipment to become raidable. Using
    these to run around naked constantly, however, will result in our rapid
   termination from existence. Also, store-bought eq is fine ONLY if you have
      nothing better, either on storage or in your guild or house chests.
 
    LAKING your own equipment to prevent others from obtaining the equipment
      when you know you are going to die is cheesy and pisses off the Gods,
    don't piss off the Gods. This also contravenes the fact that you must be
                           wearing full raid slots.

    Thieves are now bound and held totally to the rules addressed above, as
                  well as the guidelines listed in Help Thief.
===========================================================================

#
"RAISE LICH" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <corpse>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Animation lasts until undead follower dies (again)
Type of spell:  Summoning

If the Necromancer has a suitable corpse at his feet, "Raise Lich"
re-animates the corpse with the formidable power of a Lich. Liches by 
nature are powerful Sorcerers, but their undead prowess allows them to 
cause considerable damage with their bare hands as well.
===========================================================================
See also: ORDER, PETS, PRESERVE, "MASS PRESERVE", EMBALM, "SENSE FOLLOWER"

#
"RAISE SHADOW" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <corpse>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Animation lasts until undead follower dies (again)
Type of spell:  Summoning

If the Necrolyte has a suitable corpse at his feet, this spell will force 
the soul of the slain back into their body, transforming them into a 
shadow. The shadow is a translucent being that attacks the enemy with the
power of its mind.
===========================================================================
See also: NECROLYTE

#
"RAISE SKELETON" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <corpse>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Animation lasts until undead follower dies (again)
Type of spell:  Summoning

"Raise Skeleton" recalls the soul of the slain to their corpse, creating a
skeleton.  Skeletons are the weakest of all undead, their strength comes 
mostly from sheer numbers.
===========================================================================

#
"RAISE SPECTRE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <corpse>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Animation lasts until undead follower dies (again)
Type of spell:  Summoning

"Raise Spectre" recalls the soul of the slain to their corpse, creating a
spectre. Spectres by nature are rogues, and they are naturally invisible.
===========================================================================
See also: ORDER, PETS, PRESERVE, "MASS PRESERVE", EMBALM, "SENSE FOLLOWER"

#
"RAISE VAMPIRE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <corpse>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Animation lasts until undead follower dies (again)
Type of spell:  Summoning

If the Necromancer has a suitable corpse at his feet, "Raise Vampire" 
infuses the corpse with the brutal power of a Vampire. Vampires by nature 
are powerful warriors and enjoy tearing into warm, mortal flesh.
===========================================================================
See also: ORDER, PETS, PRESERVE, "MASS PRESERVE", EMBALM

#
"RAISE WRAITH" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <corpse>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Animation lasts until undead follower dies (again)
Type of spell:  Summoning

If the Necromancer has a suitable corpse at his feet, "Raise Wraith" causes 
the corpse to return to existence as a wraith. Wraiths by nature are 
Sorcerers, but their power varies from animation to animation. They are 
somewhat physically weak and cannot withstand much damage to their fragile 
forms, but they have the potential to be deadly foes.
===========================================================================
See also: ORDER, PETS, PRESERVE, "MASS PRESERVE", EMBALM, "SENSE FOLLOWER"

#
"RAISE ZOMBIE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <corpse>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Animation lasts until undead follower dies (again)
Type of spell:  Summoning

"Raise Zombie" recalls the soul of the slain to their corpse, creating a
zombie.  Zombies are weaker warriors than vampires, their strength comes 
mostly from sheer numbers.
===========================================================================

#
RAGELORD (Specialization)
===========================================================================
As the name implies, Ragelord's have increased their skills when it comes
to the control of their baser instincts to flurry and rage. With the
enhanced ability to channel these skills, they have learnt to automatically
berserk should they become wounded in battles, increasing their chance to
survive the encounter. Due to this intense focus upon themselves and the 
battle, they are able to more easily avoid the more harmful attack affects
of their opponents. They are therefore while still primarily defensive in
nature, able to tune themselves to a more effective offensive captability.

Skills
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
31st Level:   Hammer Mastery
51st Level:   Grapple

===========================================================================
See also: GRAPPLE, "HAMMER MASTERY", SPEC_LIST, BERSERKER, SKILL_BERSERKER

#
RANDOM "RANDOM EQUIMENT" "RANDOM MOB" "RANDOM ZONE"
===========================================================================
The chaotic nature of Duris manifest's itself in the spontaneous creation
of creatures, areas and equipment in places not generally found.

Random Equipment
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
These items are forged by the swirl of powers inherent upon that moment of
death, and can occasionally be found on the corpses of defeated creatures.

Random Mobs
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tossed through the ether from latent world magic's gone awry, creatures far
from home can be found wandering lost on the lands. Beware approaching 
these bewildered souls, as fear may drive them past all reasoning and
sanity into beings of unrivaled aggression and power.

Random Zones
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Powerful shifts and changes within the earth's crust toss up areas from the
depths. Still half buried, these require a shovel and some hard digging
before they can be accessed and explored to find what treasures and beasts
may lurk hidden and lie within.

===========================================================================
See also: ZONE, MOB, EQUIPMENT, DIG

#
"RANGE SPECIALIST" (Skill)
===========================================================================
This lets you specialize in missile weapons, and makes you more likely
to hit opponents with them.
===========================================================================
See also: ARCHERY, "RANGE WEAPONS"

#
RANGER (Sub-Class of: Fighter)
===========================================================================
Rangers are Fighters who are trained and skilled at woodland survival and
techniques. They are one with nature and they are the best in the world at
two-weapon combat. Although, Rangers are not quite as generally skilled in 
battle as Warriors are, they have the advantage of possessing limited 
spell-casting abilities. These abilities are granted to them once they 
progress upward in level and become powerful enough to use the magic as a 
reward for their mastery of woodland survival.

Allowable races:  Human, Grey Elf, Half-Elf, Centaur
Innate abilities: Outdoor Sneak
Equipment usage:  Rangers have their own classification of item
                  restriction. They can use almost all weapons and most
                  types of armor. They are somewhat limited in their use of
                  miscellaneous magical items.     

&+RNOTE&n: Rangers must stay good aligned or else they lose their magical
     abilities until they mend their ways.
===========================================================================
See also: SKILL_RANGER

#
"RANGE WEAPONS" (General Information)
===========================================================================
Range weapons fall in two categories:

&+cFire weapon (bow, crossbow, etc)&N
To fire a weapon you must be wielding a firing weapon (bow, crossbow, etc) 
and have a quiver with ammunition. You must possess the correct type of 
missile for your particular weapon in order to be able to fire. The number 
of missiles fired depend on the weapon. Elves tend to be very good with 
range weapons.

Syntax:    fire <missile> <target> <direction>

&+cThrown weapon (dagger, spear, axe, etc)&N
To throw a weapon you need to wield it and it must be a throwable weapon. 
If you wield two weapons with the same name, you will throw both. The number 
of attacks is almost the same as when you fight hand-to-hand.

Syntax:    throw <weapon> <target> <direction>
===========================================================================
See also: FIRE, THROW, ARCHERY

