#
REAVER (Sub-Class of: Fighter)
===========================================================================
Reavers are a unique mix of both warrior and spell-caster. They have left
behind their sorcerous professions, and have instead turned to the powers
of the old gods, studying their ways and natures. As such, they have
forgotten much of their old spells in preference of their new direction, 
however they still retain some core spells from their forgotten pasts. In
their thirst for further power, they also too have looked at the ways of
warriors to enhance their abilities and have training their bodies and
minds to gain physical battle skills to enhance their offensive capacity.

Allowable races:        Drow, Orc, Goblin.
Equipment usage:        Like all classes on Duris, Reavers have their own
                        specific item restrictions. They do however have 
                        quite a wide range of equipment options being able
                        to utilize to some extent, both the weaponry and
                        armor of warriors along with the magical garb of
                        a spellcaster.  
                        
===========================================================================
See also: MAGIC, WARRIOR, SORCERER, SKILL_REAVER

#
REBOOT CRASH (General Information)
===========================================================================
The term "reboot" refers to when the game is manually shut down for a short
period of time and restarted. Restarting the game causes all monsters,
areas and equipment to be reloaded as if the game had not been touched. If
a reboot occurs while you are logged on, you will reappear after the reboot
in the same location as you were immediately before the reboot. This is
independent of where you last rented.

The term "crash" refers to when the games simply shuts down without warning
due to reasons outside of the gods' control. As in a reboot, all monsters,
areas, and equipment will load after a crash. The main difference between
the two is that you will appear in the game at the last place that you
rented or camped following a crash.

PLAYER CORPSES WILL RE-LOAD FOLLOWING A REBBOT OR CRASH. REIMBURSEMENTS
FOR DYING BEFORE EITHER WILL NOT BE GIVEN. CORPSES WILL DECAY AS NORMAL.
THERE ARE NO REIMBURSEMENTS FOR ITEMS "LOST" DUE TO A REBOOT OR CRASH.
===========================================================================
See also: DECAY, REIMBURSEMENT, POLICIES

#
RECALL
===========================================================================
Syntax:  recall [<number> | <pattern>]

Use this command to search for private messages, ie. tells, group-says or
gccs you have received. Number specifies the amount of lines to display,
pattern can be given to list only matching lines, for example containing
name of whoever told you something. Remember to include * characters in
pattern, for example 'recall *joe*' will list all messages from player
called Joe.
===========================================================================
See also: GSAY, TELL, GCC

#
RECITE SCROLLS
===========================================================================
Syntax:  recite <scroll> [<target>]

This command is used to invoke the magic in a scroll.  Your target can be
an object, a creature, or nothing (which may be yourself). Because scrolls
are magical, they will have no effects if used in a "No Magic" room.
===========================================================================
See also: MAGIC-USER, MAGIC

