#
SCORE ATTRIBUTES
===========================================================================
"Score" is a command used to show the current state of your character.
It will show you your level, race, class, current hit
point/mana/movement ratios, the various types and amounts of currency
you are carrying, your playing time, your title (if any), your group
leader or who you are following, your followers (if any), your
position, and the spells you are affected by (if any).

"Attributes" is a command used to show more information on your
character.  It shows your level, race, class, age, height, weight,
strength, intelligence, wisdom, dexterity, constitution, armor class,
hitroll, damroll, alignment, saving throws, player flags, wimpy level,
and load carried.
===========================================================================

#
SCOUNDREL
===========================================================================
The scoundrel, long coveting the ways of its brethren, the assassins and
thieves has trained and extended some similar traits of their kind. Their
ability now far exceeds the limits of their other Bard counterparts, and
are now able to rise and excel in these skills to a higher level.

Skills
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
31st level:     Dodge (Extended)
31st level:     Backstab (Extended)
52nd level:     Trip

Innate Abilities
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
31st level:     Enhanced Flee

===========================================================================
See also: BARD, SPEC_LIST, TRIP, FLEE, DODGE, BACKSTAB

#
SCRIBE (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         hold quill | hold spellbook
                scribe <spell>       : copy from book/scroll in inventory
	        practice <spell>     : learn a spell from a teacher in room


In order for a Magic-User to cast spells, they must first possess a
spellbook filled with spells to cast. To do this, you must have a spellbook, 
quill and either a teacher mob or another player's already scribed 
spellbook. Once you are holding both the quill and book, you can start to 
write them in your spellbook by typing one of the above commands, depending 
on who you are copying/learning from. Proficiency at scribing affects how 
quickly a Magic-User will inscribe new spells into his/her spellbook when 
practicing or adding new spells.
===========================================================================
See also: PRACTICE, MAGIC-USER, MYSTICS, "SPELL SYSTEM", "SPELL SLOT", "SPELL CIRCLE"

#
SEARCH (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:  search <container>
         search

There are times when items, items in containers, doors or even creatures
and players are not evident. This command may or may not reveal such things
to you. You may have to search several times to find what is hidden, this
is based on how intelligent of a creature you are.
===========================================================================
See also: HIDE

