#
SLEEP (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Enchantment

A successful spellcast will cause the victim to fall magically asleep for a
time. A victim under this spell cannot awaken on their own; they must wait 
for the spell to wear off or be awoken by taking damage.
===========================================================================
See also: WAKE

#
"SLOW POISON" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

This spell causes a person afflicted by poison to feel the ravages of the
poison's sickness move through their body more slowly.
===========================================================================
See also: POISON

#
SLOWNESS (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Enchantment

This spell causes the victim to move more slowly in combat. It does not
dispel the "haste" spell, but can counter its effects.
===========================================================================
See also: HASTE

#
SMELTING (Skill)
===========================================================================
Smelting is one of the skills known to the Alchemist Class. It allows you
to merge pieces of ore into larger ones. This is helpful in order to fulfil
the requirements needed to forge various items.

A foundry is required to smelt ore, this can be innately created by any
alchemist.

To smelt ore simply follow these steps:
   Create a foundry.
   Open the forge.
   Put the ore you wish to smelt into the forge.
   Smelt the ore.

The syntax for using this skill is &+Ysmelt&n.

Both the skill in smelting and level of the alchemist will determine how
successful the outcome is. It is well known that less experienced
alchemists often end up with nothing but ashes when trying to use
this skill.
===========================================================================
See Also: MINE, FORGE, ALCHEMIST, SKILL_ALCHEMIST

#
SNAILSPEED (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Animal

"Snailspeed" causes the victim's maximum movements to be reduced, with the
amount dependent on the proficiency of the caster.
===========================================================================

#
SNEAK (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         sneak (for Assassin, Unholy-Piper, Bard)
                sneak off

This allows you to move silently from one place to another. A person who 
sneaks successfully will be able to travel (for a period of time) without 
anyone taking notice of his or her arrival or departure. As with most 
learned skills, there is always a chance that you will not sneak 
successfully and, with this particular command, you will be unable to tell 
if it has worked or not. You can quit sneaking with "sneak off."
===========================================================================
See also: HIDE, UD-SNEAK, "SQUERRIKS SNEAKY WAYS", "OUTDOOR SNEAK"

