#
SPEAK
===========================================================================
Syntax:  speak <language>
         speak

This command lets you change which language you are currently speaking to a
new one by typing "speak <language>."  Note that you cannot change if you
are not proficient enough in the target language. "Speak" alone shows a
list of your language proficiencies, also your currently spoken language.
===========================================================================
See also: LANGUAGES

