  -Unholy-Piper: Disharmonist, Scoundrel, Minstrel
  -Warrior: Swordsman, Guardian

NOTE: Use help <specname> for information on a specific specialization.
===========================================================================
See also: SPECIALIZATIONS, SKILLS, INNATE

#
SPECIALIZATIONS SPECIALIZE (General Information)
===========================================================================
Upon reaching level 30, you may "specialize" you character, meaning to 
choose a path or skill-set. After you have decided what specialization you
would like to be, you must find the proper "teacher" mob of your class to
aid you in your specialization. Then, you must type "spec <specname>" to 
confirm your choice. &+RWARNING&n: Once you specialize you cannot later 
change your choice!

NOTE: Not all classes have specializations available.
      Use help <specname> for information on a specific specialization.
===========================================================================
See also: SPEC_LIST, TOGGLE_SHOWSPEC

#
SPELLBIND (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax: <spellbind item_name>
	<spellbind> Lets the alchemist see accumulated power

With this powerful enchantment skill the alchemist can empower an item
with mystical energies enhancing the properties of the item. The rate to 
which the item is improved is based on the level and skill of the 
alchemist. The first stat of the item will also be raised more than the 
second stat of the item.

When an item has been enchanted the magical energies make it impossible to
repair. Even a failed attempt will render the item unrepairable. There is 
also a chance that the item will be damaged in the process.

In order to gain the power necessary to spellbind items the alchemist needs 
to harvest power by killing creatures greater than 10 levels below his own 
level. The alternative is to gain this power by fragging. With each 0.1 
frags the alchemist can spellbind one item. 
===========================================================================
See also: ALCHEMIST

#
"SPELL CIRCLE" (General Information)
===========================================================================
Just as in AD&D, Duris has placed its spells in various levels called
circles. As a caster gains in level, he learns more of the magical arts and
has a larger repertoire of spells to choose fro . These new spells exist in
"Circles". At any given level, a caster can draw from a specified number of
circles and can memorize/pray/tupor/assimilate/commune for a certain number 
of spells in each circle which fit into "Spell Slots". As a caster's level 
increases he learns more magic and can draw from more circles as well as 
regenerate more spells from each circle. The circles are gained as follows:

        Level 1 -1st Circle
        Level 6 -2nd Circle
        Level 11 -3rd Circle
        Level 16 -4th Circle
        Level 21 -5th Circle
        Level 26 -6th Circle
        Level 31 -7th Circle
        Level 36 -8th Circle
        Level 41 -9th Circle
        Level 46 -10th Circle
        Level 51 -11th Circle
        Level 56 -12th Circle

See the specific help files on each class to find out which spells belong
to each circle for any given class. There is a slight chance of spell
failure for the last circle learned.
===========================================================================
See also: MEMORIZE, PRAY, COMMUNE, ASSIMILATE, TUPOR, "SPELL SLOT", 
          "SPELL FAILURE", "SPELL SYSTEM", "SPELL SLOT"

#
"SPELL FAILURE" (General Information)
===========================================================================
A caster who has practiced specific spells for a long period of time
becomes very skilled at casting the spells. He is able to work his magic
without fear of error or incorrectly invoking magic. So, as he gains in
levels, the lower spells become second nature to him. However, when he is
charged with learning new spells of a more complicated nature than he is
used to, he may find it difficult to cast without error. So, casters will
find that they sometimes cannot cast a spell of their highest circle every
time they try. Expect spell failure as you are learning the spells and are
not yet a master of their powers.
===========================================================================
See also: "SPELL CIRCLE", "SPELL SLOT", "SPELL SYSTEM", MEMORIZE, PRAY,
          COMMUNE, TUPOR, ASSIMILATE

#
"SPELL SLOT" (General Information)
===========================================================================
A caster is able to hold a certain number of spells in each spell circle, 
dependent on level. Each spell occupies one spell slot in the given circle. 
Casters that commune, assimilate or tupor cannot choose what spells will
fill their specific slots, unlike casters that memorize and pray.
===========================================================================
See also: "SPELL CIRCLE", "SPELL SYSTEM", MEMORIZE, PRAY, COMMUNE, TUPOR,
           ASSIMILATE

#
"SPELL SYSTEM" (General Information)
===========================================================================
Duris, in its attempt to improve on the standard, stock DikuMUDs that 
already exist throughout the Internet, has moved away from the traditional 
mana system. In its place, the Duris Forgers have implemented a system very 
similar to that used in the AD&D game. Rather than a pool of mana from 
which any spell can be drawn, casters on Duris must memorize/pray/commune/
assimilate or tupor spells. These spells are divided into different "Spell
Circles" limiting the spells that a caster/semi-caster can draw upon. At 
level 1, a caster is proficient in one spell circle and is allotted one 
"Spell Slot" from that circle which he can regain via one of the methods 
listed above. As he gains in levels, the numbers of slots available in each 
circle increases as does the number of circles in which the caster is 
proficient. The caster has available to him a number of spells at each 
circle which he can regenerate. He simply chooses those spells which he 
wishes to use then must fill his reservoir in one of the mentioned ways. 
The slots can be used up on all different spells or all on the same spell or 
any combination of spells. These spells are then a part of the caster's mind 
and can be called upon at any time. Once a spell is cast it  s no longer 
memorized or prayed for. It becomes a spell that needs to be memorized again. 
It cannot be cast again until it is re-memorized or re-prayed for.
===========================================================================
See also: "SPELL CIRCLE", MEMORIZE, PRAY, ASSIMILATE, COMMUNE, TUPOR

#
"SPELL, DEXTERITY" (Spell)
