#
STANCES
===========================================================================
Syntax: <stance none|offensive|defensive>

A player can make use of stances to increase his defensive and offensive 
capabilities when fighting. The offensive stance will raise all skills 
flagged offensive by a set number and all defensive skills will be lowered 
by the same number. The reverse is used when going into the defensive 
stance. Stances are later used when dealing with group formations and will 
then deal other bonuses depending on which formation was chosen. 

If someone other than the group leader, which is defined by the person 
everyone follows, uses a stance while the group is not in formation then 
that person will not be able to follow the group leader.

Something that should be noted when using stances is that it affects the 
skill dodge. A high skill in dodge will make the character harder to bash 
and this value goes up if you are in defensive stances and it goes down if 
you are in offensive stance. 
===========================================================================
See also: Formations, Group

#
"STANZA OF THE FURY" (Song)
===========================================================================
Area of effect:	Group
Aggressive:	No
Cumulative:	No	
Duration:	Dependent on proficiency of singer
Type of song:	Generic

"Stanza of the Fury" elevates the amount of adrenaline produced by those
in the group, increasing their combat abilities.  As the Piper becomes
more skillful in this song, it can also cause those in his/her group
to move much quicker in combat.
===========================================================================
See also: INSTRUMENT, WAIL, PIPER, SKILL_PIPER

#
STATS STATISTICS (General Information)
===========================================================================
Duris character abilities are on a bell-curved 1-100 scale. The number 
given to any statistic is a measure of how you rate WITHIN YOUR OWN RACE. A 
Gnome with 100 Strength, for example, is as strong as it is possible for a 
Gnome to be, without major magical enhancement. However, even a moderately 
strong Ogre would be vastly stronger than a 100 strength Gnome. Ogres are 
known for strength, Gnomes are not. The conversion factors for a given race 
are hidden and not available to players. Experimentation will no doubt 
discover some of them, and checking the help on a race will give you an 
idea where their strengths and weaknesses lie. All races of Duris use the 
same scale (1-100) and all races have their own set of conversion factors. 
Do not bother asking a God what these factors are, most won't know.
Furthermore, the ones that do know will not tell you, experiment and find 
out.
===========================================================================
See also: STRENGTH, DEXTERITY, AGILITY, CONSTITUTION, POWER, INTELLIGENCE,
          WISDOM, CHARISMA, LUCK

# 
STEAL (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         steal <object> <victim>
                steal coins <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes

"Steal" is used to take items or money from other creatures without their 
knowledge or consent. The success of your theft will depend on your 
proficiency and whether or not the person is conscious.

NOTE: Stealing from other players can only be done once you reach a certain 
level.
===========================================================================
See also: RAID

