#
THIEF (Specialization)
===========================================================================
Thieves are masters of stealth, deceit, concealment, and they'll relieve
you of your valuables if you don't watch your purse. The main cause of
thieves is to take what is yours and to make it their own, preferably
without their victims knowing about it. But if backed into a corner,
thieves can be deadly enemies and are more than capable of fighting their
way out of tight spots. The dreaded thief is also renowned for its ability
to pick locks, alter their identity, to vanish into the shadows, not to
mention hunting their prey to the ends of the world to get what they want.

Thieves are held fully to the rules listed in Help Raid for equipment
guidelines, and while engaged in pstealing or pkilling they are considered
"primary" characters and as such must wear the best equipment available up
to and including removing equipment from their other characters to meet
these guidelines. This DOES include artifacts, uniques, and iouns, *unless*
they are not usable by a thief.  

ALL items stolen by a thief must be worn by the thief *unless* they cannot
use the object or are currently wearing better in that slot, in which case
it may be stored or given away.

ALL slots must be filled on a thief when at all possible, this includes
removing pieces of equipment from other characters that may not make much
sense on a thief.

For example, if you have the max_int ioun on another character, you MUST
remove it and put it on your thief when playing it. The only exception is
if the thief is currently wearing another ioun.

Thieves CANNOT be shared by multiple players at once. If any thief is found
being shared, they will be terminated whether or not the owner is online. 
Trying to get by these rules will be met with harsh consequences. If you
are unsure about what is legal or not, ask a god.

Skills
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
30th: Trip
30th: Dirttoss
30th: Listen
30th: Feign Death
36th: Enhanced Riposte
51st: Hamstring
56th: Evade
===========================================================================
See also: ROGUE, SKILL_ROGUE, CLASSES, SKILLS, ASSASSIN, BRAVO 

#
THRI-KREEN (General Information)
===========================================================================
Thri-Kreen are sometimes called "Mantis Warriors" they are an insect race
that looks very much like a giant praying mantis, only with 4 praying arms
and 2 legs for walking. The Thri-Kreen are about 7 feet tall and up to 11
feet long, however they do not weight much, and are there for considered
medium in size. 

Thri-Kreen are desert dwelling nomadic warriors that are neutral in most of
their dealings with other races. On Duris, this means that some of them will
be with the forces of good, some with evil.

Thri-Kreen having 4 arms 4 hands and thus, can wield up to 4 weapons at a
time including 2 2-handed weapons, or a bow and 2 weapons or any combo.
Thri-Kreen can also wear 4 sets of wrist-eq, 2 sets of hand wear, 2 sets of
sleeve eq. But they have no true fingers, and no ears. So they can not wear
any ear-rings or normal finger rings, and due to the odd nature of their
body and feet, they can not wear anything on their feet or body armor.

Thri-Kreen are a neutral born race, which means they can pick the path in
life in which they will walk, so, a Thri-Kreen must chose this path when he
is created.

Class list:       Warrior.
Statisticss:      Quite strong, tall and thin, very quick, also very high
                  in agility and very high dex. they are swift and fearsome
                  warriors.
Innate abilities: infravision, ultravision, leap, poison bite.

Thri-Kreen are extremely vulnerable to the cold and cold-based spells, the 
shock to their systems may in many cases even cause minor paralysis. Due to
their exoskeletal nature, thri-kreen are somewhat weaker than endoskeletal
races, and therefore will not receive certain stat bonus granted by various
spells and active skills.
===========================================================================
See also: RACES, RACEWARS, INNATE, INFRAVISION, ULTRAVISION

#
"THROAT CRUSH" (Skill)
===========================================================================
Aggressive:     Yes

Crushing a victim's throat cripples their ability to speak effectively for 
a short time, which in turn takes away their ability to cast spells.
===========================================================================

#
THROW (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         throw <weapon> <target> <direction>

In order to throw a weapon, you must be wielding it and it must be a 
throwable type weapon. If you wield two weapons with the same name, you will 
throw both. The number of attacks is almost the same as when you fight 
hand-to-hand.
===========================================================================
See also: "RANGE WEAPONS", FIRE

#
"THROW LIGHTNING" (Innate)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

"Throw lightning" invokes the forces of nature to make lightning strike the
intended victim. It is therefore only possible to cast this spell when you
are outside and while it is raining (or worse), as the spell causes a
massive bolt of lightning to hurl itself from the rain clouds overhead,
striking the intended victim and causing considerable damage.
===========================================================================
See also: "CONTROL WEATHER", WEATHER

#
THROWPOTION (Skill)
===========================================================================

     SYNTAX : throwpotion <potion> <target>

Once you have mixed your potion, you will want to throw it at your target,
and to do this, the potion you wish to throw must be in your inventory.
Your accuracy at hitting your victim, instead of others in your group or
even yourself will grow with your skill and level. As an example, if you
had a chill touch potion and you wished to throw it at the mob in the room
called "hunter", type: throwpotion chill hunter
===========================================================================
See also: THROW, MIX, SKILL_ALCHEMIST

#
THUG (MultiClass)
===========================================================================
A Thug is a multi-class Rogue/Mercenary.
===========================================================================
See Also: ROGUE, MERCENARY, MULTI-CLASS

#
TIME
===========================================================================
"Time" gives you the current game-time of Duris. There are:

        7 days in a week
       35 days in a month
       17 months in a year

and 60 real-life seconds for each game-hour. Some situations, such as the
opening of the Tharnadia city gates, are also dependent on game-time.
===========================================================================
See also: CALENDAR, DAY

#
"TITAN" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: one titan
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

When cast, "Titan" creates a illusionary 60 foot tall replica of the 
caster that will carry out his or her orders without question until ether 
the victim dies or the illusion has taken enough damage!
===========================================================================

#
TITLES (General Information)
===========================================================================
Duris is a fantasy based mud and as such we expect the players to have 
fantasy based titles, if they have them at all. What a proper title is
might be different for most but there are some basics. 

	-Do not use foul language
	-Do not use racial slurs
 	-Keep it in character

Duris may not be a role-play mud but that does not mean we don't work hard 
to try to cultivate a good fantasy feeling while online. Any title that 
breaks this is considered a bad title and may be subject to change. If guild 
ranks are out of line the guild is subject to be disbanded.
===========================================================================
See also: GUILD

#
TOGGLE (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle            (displays current toggle status)
                toggle <option>   (change current toggle status for option)

This command is used to change the current state of the options your
character may use. The default for all new characters is to have the 
majority of these options set to OFF. More comprehensive help may be found 
by typing "help <toggle_optionname>". The following options may be set:

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                           STATUS of toggles.                               
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
Tell        : ON     |     Brief Mode  : ON     |     No Locate   : OFF    
SmartPrompt : OFF    |     Compact Mode: OFF    |     Wimpy Level : OFF    
Shout       : ON     |     Echo        : ON     |     Vicious     : OFF    
Petition    : ON     |     Paging      : OFF    |     Save Notify : ON     
Anonymous   : OFF    |     Screen Size :  24    |     Terminal    : ANSI   
Map         : ON     |     Old SmartP  : OFF    |     Show Titles : ON     
Battle Alert: OFF    |     Kingdom View: OFF    |     Ship Map    : OFF    
Take        : ON     |     Terse Battle: OFF    |     QuickChant  : ON     
Project     : OFF    |     AFK         : OFF    |     NChat       : ON     
Hint Channel: OFF    |     Group Needed: OFF    |     Showspec    : ON
Web Info    : OFF    |               
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

===========================================================================

#
TOGGLE_AFK (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle afk

Setting this option to ON will automatically mark you as AFK. Any action
you perform will remove the AFK marker. Be warned, if you remain AFK for
too long, you will "Void". It is always best to be certain you are in a
safe place (i.e. your guildhall) before you AFK.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, AFK, IDLE

#
TOGGLE_ANONYMOUS ANONYMOUS (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle anonymous

This toggle allows you to hide your level and class from all other mortal
players, which gives the MUD a more realistic feel. After all, how would
someone on the street know what class or level you were unless you revealed
it? Evils do not have the option of togging this.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, WHO

#
"TOGGLE_BATTLE ALERT" (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle battle alert

When this option is on and if you are engaged in combat, you will see green
brackets encasing your physical attacks and red brackets surrounding your
enemy's attacks.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
TOGGLE_BRIEF (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle brief

This toggle turns on and off room descriptions. If you have Brief Mode
toggled ON but you wish to see a room description, type 'look room'.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
TOGGLE_COMPACT (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle compact

This option scrunches your display a little bit, allowing you to see more 
on the screen at once.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
TOGGLE_ECHO (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle echo

This toggle option allows you to view your written communications as they 
appear to others.
If, for example, you type:

                say Hi, Fizzwig
  
You would see:
                You say 'Hi, Fizzwig!
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
"TOGGLE_GROUP NEEDED" (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle group needed
 
This option allows you to set a flag for your name on the "Who" list to
inform all other players of your racewar side that you are looking for a
group.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, GROUP, WHO

#
TOGGLE_HINT CHANNEL
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle hint channel

With this option toggled ON, you will periodically see HINTS useful for
newer players to the game appear on the screen.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
TOGGLE_MAP (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle map

This command will turn your view of ANSI wilderness maps on and off.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
"TOGGLE_NCHAT" (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle nchat

Setting this option ON will allow you to hear and converse on the "Newbie" 
chat channel. This is a useful feature for those first starting out on Duris 
or those that are new to mudding in general. 

NOTE: After achieving a specified number of levels, "Nchat" will no longer
      be available to you. 
NOTE: If you are a higher level player with an interest in helping new
      players to the game by providing useful information and answering
      questions on nchat, please contact a god and have this channel 
      activated for you.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, NCHAT, NEWBIE

#
TOGGLE_NOLOCATE (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle nolocate

This option determines whether or not anyone can use you as a target for 
teleport spells. Evil and Undead aligned player's do not have the option of
turning this feature ON.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
PAGING TOGGLE_PAGING (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle paging

When this option is OFF, you will have the ability to scroll larger text 
files down your screen by hitting the enter key. When this option is ON,
if the text being displayed is small enough or you have set your screen
size large enough, you will be able to see the entire text in one
continuous stream. You may set your screen size by using the 
"toggle screensize" option.
===========================================================================
See also: "TOGGLE_SCREEN SIZE", TOGGLE

#
TOGGLE_PETITION (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle petition

When this option is OFF, you will be deaf to the petition channel.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, PETITION

#
"TOGGLE_SAVE NOTIFY" (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle save notify

Turning this option ON will allow you to receive notification that your
character has been automatically saved by the MUD code. Duris saves all
characters periodically (as do the Gods), but it is also a good idea to
save your character manually after events such as levels, frags or potions.
===========================================================================
See also: SAVE, TOGGLE

#
"TOGGLE_SCREEN SIZE" (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle screensize <size>
                toggle screensize default
                toggle screensize off

This lets you determine the size of the MUD's output to you (for use with 
the paging option), or turn it off entirely. The default is 24 lines.
===========================================================================
See also: PAGING, TOGGLE

#
"TOGGLE_SHIP MAP" (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle ship map

Setting this option ON will allow you to see the map while sailing on a 
ship, whether it be your ship or someone else's.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, SHIP

#
TOGGLE_SHOUT (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle shout

This toggle affects your ability to "Shout" and hear other people's shouts.
===========================================================================
See also: SHOUT, TOGGLE

#
TOGGLE_SHOWSPEC (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle showspec
 
This option allows you to see what player's are "specialized" on the "Who"
list instead of their regular class listings.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, SPECIALIZATION, WHO, CLASSES

#
"TOGGLE_SHOW TITLES" (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle show titles
 
If you turn this option OFF, you will no longer see titles belonging to
other people in the room with you (if they have titles in the first place).
This can greatly help in reducing spam if you are in a large, rapidly
moving group.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
TOGGLE_SMARTPROMPT (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle smartprompt

This option allows you to select whether your prompt displays after any
new output (OFF), or just when you input a new command (ON).  The ON
setting is to reduce spam (i.e. screen roll that makes it difficult to 
absorb the MUD's output).
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
TOGGLE_TAKE (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle take
 
This option allows you to automatically refuse to be given items from other
people.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, TAKE

#
TOGGLE_TELL (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle tell

This toggle affects your ability to use the "Tell" communication channel.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, TELL

#
TOGGLE_TERSE (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle terse

This option condenses all physical hits during battle into one line per 
character, with the number of hits in parentheses (). It helps to
cut down on spam.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
TOGGLE_WIMPY (Command)
===========================================================================
&+RThis command is currently disabled&n
Syntax:         toggle wimpy <number of hitpoints>

This is an auto-flee option. If your hitpoints drop below the specified
level in your wimpy toggle, you will attempt to flee.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, FLEE, WIMPY

#
TOGGLE_VICIOUS (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle vicious

When this option is ON, you will kill the mortally wounded during battle. 
When this toggle is OFF, you will disengage from battle when whoever or 
whatever you are fighting is incapacitated.

NOTE: Paladins do not have the option of turning "Vicious" ON, as it is
      against their moral training.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE

#
TOGGLE_WEBINFO
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle webinfo

In the interests of providing an informative and interactive website, we
develop and show statistics about such things as Top Players, PvP kills and
equipment worn during raids on the website.

This toggle allows us to display more information over and above the
general, non-sensitive information like frag and experience progress. One
of the things toggling this setting to OFF will restrict is EQ display, and
other such more specific character information.

Please note, that any such information shown on the website has an 30
minute delay before release.

If you do not wish more specific information shown, please ensure that this
option is set to OFF. It is by default OFF.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, WEBSITE

#
TOLM (General Information)
===========================================================================
"Tolm" is often referred to a player on Duris, who can often be found
repeating such phrases as "wuss", "enjoy", "rofl", and "at once". If in
close contact with Tolm, one should be aware he commonly passes large
amounts of gaseous flatulence, causing a tremendous stench to fill the room
and killing all those within it. Choosing to follow Tolm can result in 
instantaneous death, as he can often times be remembered as spamming 
through a high aggro area and leaving his comrades behind. In reality,
though, Tolm is simply a bot created by the gods of Duris for their 
amusement. Paying close attention, one might notice his responses to things 
are quite limited, as shown above. Great care should be taken when dealing
with Tolm. 
===========================================================================
See also: SPAM, KENON, KVARK

#
TOTEMS (General Information)
===========================================================================
Totems are required by Shamans to cast their spells, as they allow them to
focus their energies into magic.

Shaman spells are divided into "spheres" -animal, elemental, and
spiritual. Lesser totems are used to cast spells in a certain sphere below
6th circle, while greater totems are used to cast those spells 6th and
over. Totems can also grant more than one sphere or high/low-level spells.
Totems must be held while casting (but not required during memorizing).

Newbie Shamans load with three totems (raven, limestone, ivory), each of
which grants the lower spells for a certain sphere. (raven =animal,
limestone =elemental, ivory =spiritual).

Higher totems can be bought at various Shaman-related stores around the
mud, as well as created by the "Minor Creation" spell.
===========================================================================
See also: SHAMAN, SKILL_SHAMAN

#
"TOWER OF IRON WILL" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <caster>
Aggressive:     N/A
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster.
Type of spell:  Enchantment

This spell causes the caster to mentally fortify himself against all mental
attacks.
===========================================================================

#
TRACK (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         track <victim>
                track off
Aggressive:     No

This allows you to track your quarry. How successfully you track down a
potential victim depends on your skill level and how far away your target
is. You can not track down specific racewar enemies, even if you happen to
know the name of a particularly notorious foe. When you have given up the
trail, you must type 'track off' in order stop tailing the quarry.
===========================================================================

#
TRAMPLE (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         trample

While mounted, this command will order your steed to "Trample" the victim,
inflicting damage with the possibility of knocking them to the ground.
===========================================================================
See also: BASH

