TRANQUILITY (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <room>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

"Tranquility" attempts to calm any persons or mob in a room.
===========================================================================

#
"TRANSFER WELLNESS" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Spiritual

This spell transfers some life from the caster to the victim. At lower
levels, the caster will lose a large amount more than the victim gains,
whereas at higher levels, it will even out.
===========================================================================

#
TRAP (Skill)
==========================================================================
Syntax:         "drop trap" and "hide trap"
Area of effect: <room>

"Trap" is a skill possessed by Thieves and specialized Mercenaries or 
Rangers. These individuals have the ability to "set" traps in a room that
when triggered by a mob or a player, will notify the character. Traps must
be purchased from Rogue shops found throughout the world.
===========================================================================

#
TRIP (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         trip <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes

This is a skill that attempts an acrobatic maneuver of tripping an opponent 
in battle. No damage is dealt, but it can have very detrimental effects, 
such as: causing a caster to abort a spell or disorienting the opponent 
long enough for the thief to make a quick retreat.
===========================================================================
See also: BASH, SPRINGLEAP

#
"TRIPLE ATTACK" (Skill) 
===========================================================================
This skill is automatic and gives you an extra attack for each combat
round, on top of the extra attacks you already get from double attack. The
likelihood of the extra attack is dependent upon your proficiency.
===========================================================================
See also: "DOUBLE ATTACK", "QUADRUPLE ATTACK"

#
TROLL "SWAMP TROLL"
===========================================================================
Swamp trolls are a huge, massive, evil, and disgusting species that are
greatly feared by all races. They are often hunted by humans, and are 
easily identifiable by their decided lack of intelligence, green hair, and 
pale-green, horned and slimy skin. Trolls' strength is horrifying and, 
since they are destructive by nature, they customarily spend all of their 
time killing and destroying. Trolls also frequently raid towns in order to 
procure slaves that become the "guests of honor" at future feasts. Trolls 
live in hot swamps and lakes, and generally band together in clans. Their 
only contact with other races occurs during acts of war. Trolls regenerate 
faster than other races do, and possess innate ultravision.

Class list:       Warrior, Shaman, Mercenary.
Statistics:       Quite strong, tall and thin, very quick, also regen hit
                  points at a truly amazing rate, however, they are almost
                  as stupid as ogres, just about as ugly too. Only what
                  passes as a genius for a troll will do well as a shaman.
Innate abilities: ultravision, bodyslam (warrior only), doorbash,
                  regeneration

&+RWarning:&n  As one of the eight evil races on Duris, trolls are
extremely difficult to play and face many hardships.  Their hometown
has been specifically designed to make life hell, and death waits
around every corner.  Trolls will most certainly encounter situations
that would be deemed "unfair" to any of the surface races.  We did
this to create a new challenge for those advances players who have
"beaten" the challenge of life on the surface world and are looking
for something more difficult.  You should NOT play a troll unless you
are a *very* advanced player and are used to the Duris style of
MUDding, or are willing to face the hardships without complaint, as it
is NOT easy.

&+RNOTE&n:  Trolls are extremely vulnerable to all fire-based spells
            and will take more damage from them.

===========================================================================
See also: RACES, RACEWARS, INNATE, INFRAVISION, BODYSLAM

#
TROPHY (General Information)
===========================================================================
Syntax:    trophy

The trophy list is a feature which lets you gain a general idea of the
amount of experience (relative to a particular mob) you are gaining  or the 
mobs you kill. The trophy ensures that you do not gain experience by 
"sitting on mobs" as the more you kill any particular mob, the less
experience you will gain for it. If you kill too many of any particular
mob, you will eventually gain no experience at all for it.

The trophy list will help your decisions by letting you know how many of
any particular mob you have already killed. If you are in a group, you
will only gain a portion of that kill added to your trophy. Therefore,
you will see percentages on your trophy list. Trophy entries will also
change colors as the amount of experience you get for a kill becomes
less and less.
===========================================================================
See also: EXPERIENCE

#
"TRUE SEEING" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <caster>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     Yes
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Divination

"True Seeing" grants the caster an increased perception. It combines the 
effects of "Detect Evil", "Detect Good", "Detect Magic", "Sense Life" and
"Detect Invisibility".
===========================================================================
See also: "DETECT GOOD", "DETECT EVIL", "DETECT MAGIC", "SENSE LIFE",
          "DETECT INVISIBILITY", "SHADOW VISION"

#
TUPOR (Innate)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         tupor (while resting or reclined and sleeping)

Allows a Harpy or Gargoyle to regain spell slots. The more relaxed and in
a state of mental and physical rest the Harpy or Gargoyle, the faster they
will regain their spell slots.
===========================================================================
See also: HARPY, CASTER, "SPELL SYSTEM", "SPELL CIRCLE", "SPELL SLOTS" 

