UNIQUES (General Information)
===========================================================================
Uniques vary in that they can be weapons, armor, and other items. Each
unique is one of a kind and therefore artifacts by nature. No unique is
alike and they all bestow different properties.

For a list of uniques, type "arti unique".
===========================================================================
See also: ARTIFACT, IOUN, FEEDING

#
UNMAKING (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <corpse>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Generic

When cast upon a nearby corpse, the caster absorbs the remaining essence 
within the body.  The caster is healed through the absorption.
===========================================================================

#
USE WANDS STAFF STAVES
===========================================================================
Syntax:  use <staff>
         use <wand> <target>

In order to invoke a wand or staff, you must first hold it in your hand, 
then employ the "use" command. Using a staff will automatically target 
everyone and everything in the room except yourself. A wand, on the other
hand, must be pointed at a target in order for you to use it. Because wands
and staves are magical items, they will not be effective if used in a
"No Magic" room.
===========================================================================
See also: HOLD, GRAB, MAGIC-USER, MYSTICS

#
VALUE
===========================================================================
Syntax:  value <item>

This will tell you what a shopkeeper will pay you for an item. Keep in mind 
that this may not always accurately reflect that item's true value.
===========================================================================
See also: SHOPS, BUY SELL, LIST

#
VAMPIRE
==========================================================================
Among the most dreaded of the undead hordes is the Vampire. Vampires are
readily identifiable by the seasoned adventurer; pallid skin, long fangs
protruding from the top of their mouths, the odor of a juicy corpse, and a
perceptible aura of pure evil. Like most undead, Vampires are only active
at nighttime or in very dark places where most mortals fear to tread. 
Vampires are notorious for draining the lifeblood of their enemies to
further their own lives and power, as well as charming less powerful
creatures to do their bidding.

Class list:       Necromancer, Sorcerer, Warlock, Warrior, Anti-Paladin,
                  Assassin, Mercenary, Thief, Dreadlord.
Statistics: 	  Vampires are extremely strong creatures, and they are
		  smarter than your average brainless corpse. A vampire's
		  true weakness is his appearance...ugly as sin.                 
Innate Abilities: ultravision, vampiric touch, bite
===========================================================================
See also: WARLOCK, SKILL_WARLOCK

#
"VAMPIRIC TOUCH" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <self>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

This spell temporarily transforms the person's hands into magical lifeforce 
leeches.  If in battle and unarmed, your hands will suck away your 
opponent's life force, granting some of it to you.

This can also be an innate ability.
===========================================================================

#
"VAMPIRIC TRANCE" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <caster>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Generic

"Vampiric Trance" infuses the caster with the power of the undead, granting 
a higher hitroll and damroll, as well as a larger number of hitpoints. The 
power of "Vampiric Touch" is granted to the caster as well. Be warned, when 
the Necromancer is in this form, they cannot control any Undead of their
own.
===========================================================================
See also: "VAMPIRIC TOUCH", PETS

