#
"WAR PRIEST" (MultiClass)
===========================================================================
A War Priest is a multi-class Warrior/Cleric.

Warriors normally do not have any spells, so there is no change to how you
acquire/pray/cast your spells when you multiclass.
===========================================================================
See Also: WARRIOR, CLERIC, MULTI-CLASS, PRAY

#
WARCRY (Skill)
===========================================================================
Preparing to go into battle, a skilled warrior lets loose with a powerful
scream, sending blood surging through the veins of the warrior and their
group. This enhances the thirst and capability for the battle.
===========================================================================

#
WARFARE (General Information)
===========================================================================
The following is a list of all HELP available that deals with battle.  Type 
"help <entry>" for more information.

Example:  "help ac" will bring up an explanation of armor class and
how it affects you.

AC "ARMOR CLASS"        AGGR AGGRESSIVE         CONSIDER
DAMAGE                  DISBAND                 EQUIPMENT
EXPERIENCE XP           FLEE                    FOLLOW
GLANCE                  GROUP                   GUILD
HOLD GRAB               INVENTORY               KILL HIT
WIMPY                   WIELD                   PRACTICE
RACEWARS PKILL          REMOVE                  SCORE ATTRIBUTES
SKILLS                  SPLIT                   TANK
THAC0                   TROPHY                  VICIOUS
WEAR                                     
===========================================================================

#
WARLOCK (Sub-Class of: Priest)
===========================================================================
Warlocks are malevolent practitioners of dark, forbidden magics that
have only been mastered by the Undead.  Their powers are based neither
in the conventional magics practiced by mortals, nor in the power of the
mind like the illithids.  Warlocks tap into the dark realm of the 
negative material plane, but the greater part of their energy comes from
the bowels of hell itself.  The nature of their power not only vanquishes
their enemies, it also increases the Warlock's own power and energy.  Any 
simple mortal attempting to dabble in such horrid sorcery would almost 
surely be annihilated immediately.

Allowable races:        Vampire, Lich, Shade

Innate Abilities:       No class-specific innate abilities.

Equipment usage:        Warlock fall under the Priest classification
                        of item restriction.  This means they are
                        restricted to use of non-edged weapons such as
                        maces, clubs and staves. They can wear almost 
                        any type of armor, but are mildly restricted 
                        in the use of miscellaneous magical items.
===========================================================================
See also: SKILL_WARLOCK, ASSIMILATE

#
WARRIOR (Sub-Class of: Fighter)
===========================================================================
Warriors have more strength than the average player, and this makes them
better at hand-to-hand combat. They possess skills of fighting that are
unequaled by members of any other class. Because they employ such finesse
in their fighting tactics, Warriors have been thought to resemble
swashbucklers or fencers when at their best. They are, in essence, the
ultimate fighter and are the best in the world at skills such as bash, 
rescue, kick, and parry. The advantages of being a warrior lie within
these skills.

Allowable races:        Human, Barbarian, Drow Elf, Grey Elf, 
                        Mountain Dwarf, Duergar Dwarf, Halfling, Gnome, 
                        Ogre, Swamp Troll, Orc, Half-Elf, Goblin, Vampire, 
                        Wight, Githyanki, Centaur, Storm Giant, Thri-Kreen,
                        Minotaur, Shade, Revenant, Death Knight,
                        Shadow Beast.
Innate Abilities:       No class-specific innate abilities.
Equipment usage:        Like all classes on Duris, Warriors have their own 
                        item restrictions. They can use most heavy armor 
                        and weapons but are more limited in using magical 
                        items.
===========================================================================
See also: FIGHTER, SKILLS, SKILL_WARRIOR, WEAPONS

#
"WATCHING WALL" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: direction
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster 
Type of spell:  Illusion

This spell creates an illusionary stone wall with many eyes in it. It will
show the caster the room from time to time. It will also show the room
to the caster if  someone is trying to destroy the wall.
===========================================================================

#
"WATER MAGUS" (Specialization)
===========================================================================
The Water Magus concentrates on utilizing the healing powers of the element
of water. His affinity with this element allows him to breathe underwater 
and to automatically conjure water for his use at will. Yet, he is not
without offensive abilities.

Innate Abilities
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
30th level:     Waterbreath, Conjure Water

Spells
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
7th circle:    Water to Life
8th circle:    Dread Wave

===========================================================================
See also: CONJURER, WATERBREATH, "CONJURE WATER", "DREAD WAVE", 
          "WATER TO LIFE"

