#
"WAY OF THE WIND" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <caster> & <player>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Teleportation

"Way of the Wind" creates an artery in the ether barely big enough to 
accommodate the caster and flings him all the way to the person he selected 
as his target, no matter how far away his target may be.
 
&+RWarning:&n Sometimes this artery can rupture, depositing the caster 
someplace completely unexpected (and perhaps very dangerous).
===========================================================================
See also: RELOCATE

#
"WEAPON ENCHANTMENT" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <weapon>
Aggressive:     N0
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Permanent
Type of spell:  Enchantment

Weapon Enchantment will enchant non-magical (non-modifying) weapons only. 
Non-modifying weapons are those that do not alter any ability. The only way
to be certain if a weapon is suitable for enchantment is to fully identify 
it.

The level of enchantment given the weapon is random, depending upon
conditions of the weather, magical energies, skill of the conjurer, and the
blessings of the gods.
===========================================================================
See also: IDENTIFY, WEATHER

#
WEAPON WEAPONS WEAPONRY (General Information)
===========================================================================
The weapons of Duris fall into several main types, and you should practice
at each to become proficient. Ability to hit with a given weapon is
improved by your proficiency with that weapon's type. Certain character
classes are prohibited from using certain weapon types. Below is a list of 
all types of weapons currently available:

                1-handed bludgeon
                1-handed slashing
                1-handed piercing
                1-handed flaying
                2-handed bludgeon
                2-handed slashing
                2-handed flaying
===========================================================================
See also: SKILLS, WARFARE

#
WEAR
===========================================================================
Syntax:  wear <object>
         wear all

"Wear" will allow you to try on some of the armor or items you have
obtained during your travels. If you are carrying more than one item of the
same time, and you want to exchange them, use the following syntax:

        remove <item>           (you now hold two of this item)
        wear 2.<item>

The last item you remove or pick up always appears at the top of your
inventory pile.
===========================================================================
See also: REMOVE, WIELD, EQUIPMENT, INVENTORY
#
"WEAPON ENCHANTMENT" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <weapon>
Aggressive:     N0
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Permanent
Type of spell:  Enchantment

"weapon enchantment" will enchant non-magical (non-modifying) weapons only. 
Non-modifying weapons are those that do not alter any ability. The only way
 to be certain if a weapon is suitable for enchantment is to fully identify 
it.

The level of enchantment given the weapon is random, depending upon
conditions of the weather, magical energies, skill of the conjurer, and the
blessings of the gods.
===========================================================================
See also: IDENTIFY, WEATHER

