#
WHIRLWIND (Skill)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         whirlwind

"Whirlwind" causes the Blademaster to suddenly speed up for a duration of
time. During this period, they will have the chance to attack their 
opponent on more occasions than normal. Although, this sudden activity will
wear down the Blademaster, tiring him and costing him movement points.
===========================================================================
See also: BLADEMASTER

#
WHO (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         who                (for listing of visible players)
                who ?              (for a complete list of valid arguments)
                who <argument>     (for a more specialized listing)
                
This command lists the people currently in the game, the level(s) they have 
achieved and their titles. Gods are listed first in the who list, then 
mortal characters.

&+RNOTE&n: On Duris, "Who" will only show the races that are of a like
     alignment. So, for example, an Evil person typing "Who" will only see
     other Evil PC's. The same holds true for Good races. 
===========================================================================

#
WIELD
===========================================================================
Syntax:  wield <weapon>

In order to use a weapon, it must be wielded. Some weapons require great 
strength to wield them and may be too heavy for your character to use. Some
classes have the skill of using two weapons. It should be noted, however, 
that the skill "double attack" (allowing you to hit twice) can only be used
with your primary weapon. You cannot hold anything else if wielding two 
weapons (unless you are a thri-kreen).
===========================================================================
See also: WEAR, REMOVE, EQUIPMENT, INVENTORY, "DUAL WIELD"

#
WIGHT (General Information)
===========================================================================
Wights are a race of undead creatures that appear to be a cross between a
zombie and a skeleton. A wight is about the same height as an ogre but
without as much mass, they are extremely strong and are fearsome foes in
battle.

Class list:       Warrior.
Statistics:       Extremely strong, huge in size and are fairly agile and
                  dexterous.
Innate abilities: Ultravision, Stone skin, Doorbash, Magical resistances.
===========================================================================
See also: WARRIOR, MERCENARY

#
WILDMAGE 
===========================================================================
The chaos mage will draw power from beyond reality, from the realm of Chaos.
This realm has immense power reserves but it is very hard to control. This 
will manifest itself by letting the mage get random results (often more 
powerful) when he casts his spell. The drawback is that he can loose control 
over the strong magic and harm random people in the room, be it friend of foe.
                
Innate Abilities
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
41st level:     Wildmagic

Spells
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
12th circle:    Chaotic Ripple
===========================================================================
See also: SORCERER, WILDMAGIC, "CHAOTIC RIPPLE"

#
WILDMAGIC (Innate)
===========================================================================
This chaotic innate ability grants the specialized Sorcerer vastly more 
powerful magical attacks, with the drawback that these attacks may randomly 
strike others in the room, whether they are friend or foe.
===========================================================================

#
WIMPY (Disabled)
===========================================================================
Syntax:         toggle wimpy <number_of_hit_points>

Toggling this on makes you flee automatically when you fall below the 
hitpoint limit while fighting. You must specify a hitpoint value for "Wimpy"
to be activated. Typing "toggle wimpy 0" will deactivate it.
===========================================================================
See also: TOGGLE, TOGGLE_WIMPY

