WINDWALK (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <caster> & <player> or <mob>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Instantaneous
Type of spell:  Teleportation

"Windwalk" is a more powerful version of the "Teleport" spell. It allows the 
caster to ride the winds and instantly travel to any player or mob within a 
distance-specific area (distance is dependant on the proficiency of the 
caster).
===========================================================================
See also: TELEPORT, GATE, "SPIRIT JUMP", "DIMENSION DOOR", "SHADOW TRAVEL"

#
WISDOM (General Information)
===========================================================================
Wisdom is many things, but primarily it is a measure of 'sense', in the
'common sense' or 'horse sense' meaning. Which is to say, it is a measure
of planning ability and learning from experience. It is the primary
attribute of all Priest types and helps all classes ability to learn.
===========================================================================
See also: STATISTICS

#
WITHER (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     Yes
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Enchantment

This spell increases the victim's effective armor class and drops
 their movement for a period of time, making it easier to hit the
victim and harder for the victim to flee.
===========================================================================

#
WIZARD 
===========================================================================
An advanced spellcaster in the ways of the Sorcerer, the Wizard can 
manipulate the essences of magics as they are tossed through the very air.
Many times they are able to disperse and dispel offensive magics aimed at 
them and sometimes even take the energies and throw the spell back from 
whence it came. The Wizard always has their spellbook close at hand and has 
imbued it with their name, they need only summon it.

Skills
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
41st level:    Arcane Block
51st level:    Arcane Riposte

Innate Abilities
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
30th level:    Summon Book
===========================================================================
See also: SORCERER, "SUMMON BOOK", "ARCANE BLOCK", "ARCANE RIPOSTE"

