#
WORMHOLE (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <caster> & <victim>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Approximately 30 seconds or until its limit is reached
Type of spell:  Generic

This spell attacks the very fabric of space and time. Given enough 
willpower, the caster can actually rip a hole in these barriers causing a 
brief passage to open to the location of their choosing. Be warned, nature
tends to correct this violation fairly quickly.
===========================================================================
See also: MOONWELL, "SHADOW GATE", ETHERPORTAL, "DISPEL MAGIC"

#
"WRAITHFORM" (Spell)
===========================================================================
Area of effect: <victim>
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Enchantment

When under the influence of Wraithform a necromancer can walk unseen by
mortal eyes, undetected by any spells. Doors and walls are meaningless to
anyone under the influence of Wraithform as well. After casting the spell, 
anything the caster happens to be wearing or carrying at the time will fall
to the ground.
===========================================================================

#
WRITE (Command)
===========================================================================
Syntax:  board write <subject>    <--one line, then press ENTER
         <balance of message>     <--your message
         /s                       <--to exit message, then press ENTER

This is used to write a message on a bulletin board or a piece of paper.
Please keep profanity out of your messages, as they can be read by anyone
in the game. You can also remove your message by using the following
syntax: "remove <message #>."

You can only delete messages written by you.

Typing /h during the balance of the message gives you a menu of options.
===========================================================================
See also: READ BOARD DELETE

#
ZEALOT (Specialization)
===========================================================================
The Zealot Cleric focuses on damage, with the Fighter skill "Offense" and 
the ability to call upon the God of Tempus to infuse them with power. Their
offensive nature allows them to be extremely adept at fighting, particulary
raiding.

Skills
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
31st level: 	Raised skill caps to 1h bludgeon
				     2h bludgeon
		 		     dodge
51st level:     Double attack 

Innate Abilities
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
30th level:     Tempus God Call

Spells
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
11th circle:    Plague

===========================================================================
See also: CLERIC, OFFENSE, "GOD CALL", PLAGUE

#
"ZONE GOD" (General Information)
===========================================================================
The "Melkivar" and "Railand" scripts, also known as "zone god scripts" are
capable of interpreting user submitted zonefiles, they are capable of
generating zonefiles on their own but more often than not a large majority
of their system processes are taken up by correcting (herein known as
rewriting) user submitted zonefiles.
===========================================================================
See also: IMMORTALS, CODER, WIZLIST, ZONES

#
ZONES (General Information)
===========================================================================
The majority of the Duris world is made up of different areas commonly
called "zones". Within these zones, a variety of things can be found, they
are filled with mobs, equipment and numerous other things. A set theme 
normally follows within each zone, created by the zone builder, and there 
several different level ranges a zone is intended for. Before exploring, it 
might be wise to type "credits".
===========================================================================
See also: CREDITS, "ZONE GOD", "AREA MAKING", MOB, WORLD

#~


